{"id": "1951", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1951", "title": "Atma", "text": "Atma is a tavern keeper of &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;.\nAtma has dark hair. She is a strong-willed, beautiful woman, and many men are aware of it.\nBiography.\nAtma ran the only tavern inside Lut Gholein. Over the years, she developed an understand with &lt;a href=\"Elzix\"&gt;Elzix&lt;/a&gt;. He would send travelers to her for drink and entertainment (often trading their wares for lodging), and she'd send them back to him for a soft bed. \nAtma had a son. When he was ill, &lt;a href=\"Lysander\"&gt;Lysander&lt;/a&gt; provided her with medicine.\nSecret of the Vizjerei.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; found itself in dire straits, as the surrounding desert became unsafe. The reduction in travelers harmed Atma's business, but she'd saved a \"nest egg\" and was therefore able to support herself. However, her son and husband were both killed by &lt;a href=\"Radament\"&gt;Radament&lt;/a&gt;. The emotional wounds were deep and became distracted, her mind always seemingly elsewhere. &lt;a href=\"Fara\"&gt;Fara&lt;/a&gt; feared that she would succumb to her despair and hatred because of her loss.\nAtma asked a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; to descend into the sewers to slay the creature. In this, they succeeded. She took some solace in knowing that her son and husband had been avenged, and in thanks, talked to Lut Gholein's townspeople. The merchants agreed to give the heroes discounts on their wares and services.\nThe heroes were able to put a rest to the evil that had plagued the desert, to which Atma gave her thanks.\nIn-game.\nAtma is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;, in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". She initiates the quest and also rewards the hero with shop discounts after the mummy has been slain. Atma can be found at the Tavern, and can heal and rejuvenate the player. Every now and then, she bursts into tears and cries hysterically for a few seconds, presumably over her husband and son. She recovers quickly, strangely enough, and wipes her face with her sleeve.\nDialogue.\nGossip about Atma.\nSome of the other locals give their thoughts concerning Atma."}
{"id": "6294", "revid": "44564686", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6294", "title": "Atma's Scarab", "text": "Atma's Scarab is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCertainly directed more towards physical fighters, Atma's Scarab is good for its high Poison Resistance and Attack Rating; it also gives a chance of casting &lt;a href=\"Amplify%20Damage\"&gt;Amplify Damage&lt;/a&gt;, an excellent &lt;a href=\"Curses\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; for physical fighters. In &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty, where most monsters come with 50% physical resistance, this proc effectively increases physical damage dealt threefold. Its low rate of activation means that Atma's Scarab is best suited to physical attackers that attack quickly, such as a &lt;a href=\"Strafe%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Strafe&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;. \nStats.\nRequired Level: 60"}
