{"id": "4230", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4230", "title": "Avoid", "text": "Avoid is a &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"This ability hones the natural defensive ability of an Amazon. If she stands still, she can predict incoming missile attacks and elude them before they reach her. Most Amazon people can do this if all of their thoughts to the task, but only a warrior trained in this skill can do this even whilst caught unaware. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThis ability is a ranged equivalent of , working in exact same way, except for it only affects ranged attacks. It allows the Amazon to avoid incoming missile attacks while standing still. Though the points drop off quickly (less than 2% per point after 8), at least one point is required as a prerequisite for\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Valkyrie\"&gt;Valkyrie&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike Dodge, Avoid works while attacking and turning; it is only disabled when actually moving.\nAny points put into this skill gives Valkyrie summons a chance to avoid missile attacks. The percentage for the Valkyrie is based on only the number of hard points allocated; +skill equipment increases the percentage for the Amazon but not the Valkyrie.\nBugs.\nIf the Amazon has an attack in progress and Avoids an enemy's attack, the remainder of the Amazon's attack has no effect. Unfortunately, the full animation sequence of the attack is completed. For example, if the Amazon launches a 10-arrow Strafe attack, but avoids an attack after arrow #2, the other 8 arrows in the sequence still show up on the screen but do not actually have any effect. The Amazon is still \"Strafe-Locked\" for the duration."}
{"id": "51610", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51610", "title": "Awakener's Urge", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"amulet\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", and part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Vithu%27s%20Urges\"&gt;Vithu's Urges&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;. It has a chance to drop as loot after completing &lt;a href=\"Kikuras%20Rapids\"&gt;Kikuras Rapids&lt;/a&gt; in I and above. Alternatively, &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt; can craft it using &lt;a href=\"Fabled%20Wisp\"&gt;Fabled Wisp&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "51968", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51968", "title": "Awakening", "text": " is a gameplay feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It can be done at the &lt;a href=\"Master%20Jeweler\"&gt;Master Jeweler&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt costs one &lt;a href=\"Dawning%20Echo\"&gt;Dawning Echo&lt;/a&gt; per gear slot and requires a rank 4 or higher &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gem\"&gt;Legendary Gem&lt;/a&gt; to be embedded in the gear. After awakening, the Legendary attribute of the item is strengthened. Awakened items are shown with a purple background. Removing the Legendary Gem will keep the awakened status of the item, but the benefits will be inactive.\nAwakening also opens up Gem Resonance slots. Resonance slots can be filled with other Legendary Gems that match the star rating of the slot. Embedded gems provide 1 resonance per rank (for 1-star Legendary Gems), 2 (for 2-star Legendary Gems), or 10 (for 5-star Legendary Gems) (11 if the main gem is 5/5 stars). Each Legendary Gem additionally has specific other Legendary Gems that when put into specific slots, will contribute towards Resonance set bonuses (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Bloody%20Reach\"&gt;Bloody Reach&lt;/a&gt; requires &lt;a href=\"Everlasting%20Torment\"&gt;Everlasting Torment&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Core\"&gt;Lightning Core&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20%26amp%3B%20Command\"&gt;Power &amp; Command&lt;/a&gt; to activate the bonuses).\n1-star gems have 2 slots, unlocked at rank 4 and 8 respectively. They require 1-star Legendary Gems. When embedded with the specific gems for the main gem, the Resonance set bonuses are:\n2-star gems have 3 slots, unlocked at ranks 4, 6 and 8 respectively. They require 1-star, 2-star and 2-star Legendary Gems. When embedded with the specific gems for the main gem, the Resonance set bonuses are:\n5-star gems have 5 slots, unlocked at ranks 4, 5, 6, 7 and 8 respectively. They require 2-star (for the first 3 slots) or 5-star (for the last 2 slots) Legendary Gems. When embedded with the specific gems for the main gem, the Resonance set bonuses are:\nHistory.\nOriginally a rank 10 Legendary Gem was required. In the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update, the requirement was lowered to rank 5, although some of the slots do not unlock until specific gem ranks are reached.\nIn the update, the minimum rank for awakening was lowered from 5 to 4. The rank requirements for opening the Resonance slots were lowered:\nOriginally only the designated Resonance gems could be embedded at all. In the December 13, 2024 update, this was changed such that any gem that matches the star rating of the slot can be embedded, but still only the designated Resonance gems will contribute towards the Resonance set bonuses."}
{"id": "24847", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24847", "title": "Awareness", "text": "Awareness\u00a0is a passive skill,\u00a0unlocked at level 66.\nIn-game.\n&lt;a href=\"Cooldown\"&gt;Cooldown&lt;/a&gt; Reduction does not help reduce the 60 seconds recharge period. The debuff is removed, however, if the character actually dies.\nFor obvious reasons, this skill is considered mandatory for &lt;a href=\"Hardcore\"&gt;Hardcore&lt;/a&gt; characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Beckon%20Sail\"&gt;Beckon Sail&lt;/a&gt; cloak provides exactly the same effect as this skill, except for its duration and healing are halved compared to Awareness, and the cooldown is doubled. These two methods do not share the cooldown with each other.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally this skill was increasing &lt;a href=\"Dodge\"&gt;Dodge&lt;/a&gt; chance over time (6% per second, resetting 1 second after successfully dodging an attack), in the same manner as &lt;a href=\"Sharpshooter\"&gt;Sharpshooter&lt;/a&gt; is increasing the &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt; chance. As of patch 2.0.5 and until 2.1, it was instead providing the Demon Hunter with\u00a0a bonus to their\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Defense\"&gt;Armor&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0equal to\u00a0\u00a0of their\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. This way, the Demon Hunter was the fifth class\u00a0to gain the \"life-saving\" passive ability\u00a0(leaving the \u00a0to be the last, as of patch 2.2.0)."}
