{"id": "3038", "revid": "53243318", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3038", "title": "Axes", "text": "An Axe is a type of weapon having a sharp edge on a single side or both sides, that is useful in breaking and cutting through more flexible material, while working well on harder material as well. It is seen in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo series&lt;/a&gt; games and is the weapon of choice for the . While axes may be &lt;a href=\"one-handed\"&gt;one-handed&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"two-handed\"&gt;two-handed&lt;/a&gt;, only in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt; the latter are a separate class.\nDiablo I.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\", all axes were two-handed and were the weapon of choice for the &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt; and, in the &lt;a href=\"Hellfire\"&gt;expansion&lt;/a&gt;, the .\u00a0\nDiablo III.\nAxes are faster than &lt;a href=\"maces\"&gt;maces&lt;/a&gt; in Diablo III, but slower than &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt;. All three weapon types can be &lt;a href=\"transmog\"&gt;transmog&lt;/a&gt;rified into each other freely.\n's &lt;a href=\"Mighty%20Weapons\"&gt;Mighty Weapons&lt;/a&gt; are often shaped like Axes."}
