{"id": "39429", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39429", "title": "Bahman the Seer", "text": "Bahman was a storyteller based in &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;. He had the ability to see into the future, and possibly past.\nBiography.\nBahman claimed to be descended from &lt;a href=\"Taan\"&gt;Taan&lt;/a&gt; scryers. He likewise claimed to be a court &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; to a lord, but after the lord's fall, Bahman's fortunes fell with him. At some point, he learnt of &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt; casting the deciding vote in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s favor, while debating the world's fate with the &lt;a href=\"Angiris%20Council\"&gt;Angiris Council&lt;/a&gt;.\nRobbed of the status he'd once enjoyed, Bahman became a storyteller in &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;. He had a working relationship with &lt;a href=\"Kharin\"&gt;Kharin&lt;/a&gt;. However, the relationship was strained, as more than once, Bahman brought her goods that brought thugs to her tent.\nSword of Justice.\nAfter the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, he added the tale of its end to his repertoire of stories. One day, after recounting its destruction, he met &lt;a href=\"Jacob%20Staalek\"&gt;Jacob Staalek&lt;/a&gt;. Through his insight, Bahman was aware of Jacob's history with &lt;a href=\"Staalbreak\"&gt;Staalbreak&lt;/a&gt;, and was able to help him evade the hunter seeking him. He bid Jacob travel northwest from Lut Gholein and walk until he saw a great peak. \nThe pair walked to Lut Gholein's northwest gate. Jacob thanked Bahman for his aid, and in turn, Bahman repayed Jacob by pickpocketing his &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;. Later that night, Bahman went to Kahrin's tent, intent on selling the blade. However, the transaction was interrupted by &lt;a href=\"Ivan\"&gt;Ivan&lt;/a&gt;, who interrogated Bahman as to where Jacob was headed. After getting the information he needed, Ivan killed him."}
