{"id": "47754", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47754", "title": "Barbarian Spirit", "text": "s are the restless spirits of fallen s that have haunted the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; around &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; since the &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;destruction of the Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nWhen Sescheron fell to the &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Army of Destruction&lt;/a&gt;, many barbarian warriors were killed in the battle. Some led the evacuate of the children and old, and most of them also lost their lives. The destruction of the Worldstone trapped the spirits of the fallen and prevented them from moving on. Even &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;five years later&lt;/a&gt;, their spirits still haunt the sites of their death.\nIn-game.\n are a gameplay feature for Frozen Tundra zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Five spirits in total can be found throughout the region \u2014 at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Everfrost%20Lake\"&gt;Everfrost Lake&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Village\"&gt;Abandoned Village&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Graveyard\"&gt;Ancient Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. Talking to one of them reveals a little bit of the events that occurred before they died."}
