{"id": "3397", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3397", "title": "Barracks", "text": "The Barracks are a part of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Monastery\"&gt;Rogue Monastery&lt;/a&gt;. It is located between the &lt;a href=\"Outer%20Cloister\"&gt;Outer Cloister&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Jail\"&gt;Jail&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Barracks are a cramped and dark with many chambers, giving the place an overall creepy atmosphere. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Malus\"&gt;Horadric Malus&lt;/a&gt; can be found here, guarded by &lt;a href=\"The%20Smith\"&gt;The Smith&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "15687", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15687", "title": "Barrel", "text": "Barrels are a recurring type of &lt;a href=\"Containers\"&gt;container&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo series&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBarrels are characterized by the following:\nDiablo I.\nBarrels can only be broken by touching them, and when smashed open, many barrels explode, dealing random damage to the character (but not monsters nearby). &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s also sometimes spawn from broken barrels. Barrels can easily kill an unwary hero, so healing before opening them is advised.\nBarrel explosions are not &lt;a href=\"traps\"&gt;traps&lt;/a&gt; that will emit a triggering sound before detonating, they explode instantly and are unavoidable.\nBarrels often are grouped together, and when one explodes, it will also detonate any other explosive varieties standing immediately adjacent to it.\nThe loot they drop, if any at all, is generally not very good and with their high chance to explode, they may not even be worth the effort.\nDiablo II.\nBarrels return in the second game, and function in exact same way as in the first game, except for their damage is much less significant, and can damage monsters as well.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28Act%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt;, there is a different type of barrel. These stone barrels are usually not found in groups, and while they do still frequently explode, they do not inflict any damage.\nDiablo III.\nIn the third game, barrels can no longer damage players; instead, barrels of oil (marked with a lit oil lamp) will explode when damaged, delivering &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"stun\"&gt;stun&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt; to nearby monsters. Normal barrels usually contain nothing, but sometimes still drop gold and spawn Skeletons.\nTorture Barrels in the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Agony\"&gt;Halls of Agony&lt;/a&gt; will always spawn &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Risen Dead&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Hungry%20Corpse\"&gt;Hungry Corpse&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Shen\"&gt;Covetous Shen&lt;/a&gt; will be found in a &lt;a href=\"Big%20Trouble%20in%20Talking%20Barrel\"&gt;huge barrel&lt;/a&gt;, which has become famous among player community. See the respective articles for details.\nMysterious Barrel is a type of container similar to &lt;a href=\"Mysterious%20Chest\"&gt;Mysterious Chest&lt;/a&gt;, a unique barrel containing &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20the%20Crows\"&gt;Mace of the Crows&lt;/a&gt;.\nSimilar containers.\nBaskets and Crates are like barrels in that they are kicked apart to open. They do not explode however, but can be &lt;a href=\"traps\"&gt;trapped&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "34948", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34948", "title": "Barrel Breaker", "text": "Barrel Breaker is a cut &lt;a href=\"event\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", intended for implementation in the third version of the also cut &lt;a href=\"Challenge%20Mode\"&gt;Challenge Mode&lt;/a&gt;, though was only a proof of concept. Here, players had to destroy as many barrels as possible while competing against other players. Some barrels were worth more points than others, and the player had to avoid hitting some barrels (this was as a means of ensuring that players didn't win through area-of-effect abilties)."}
