{"id": "2494", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2494", "title": "Bartuc the Bloody", "text": "Bartuc the Bloody is the leader of a third wave of &lt;a href=\"Council%20Member%20%28Baal%29\"&gt;Council Members (Baal)&lt;/a&gt; summoned by &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Throne of Destruction&lt;/a&gt;. Bartuc represents &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal's&lt;/a&gt; rundown before the final battle, and is accompanied by numerous council members. Possessing high lightning and fire resist is vital when fighting him and his ilk.\nBonus:\nWarlord of Blood?\nIt is possible that Bartuc was once the &lt;a href=\"Warlord%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Warlord of Blood&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei\"&gt;Vizjerei&lt;/a&gt; Mage who was in rivalry with his brother, &lt;a href=\"Horazon\"&gt;Horazon&lt;/a&gt;. However, this is not certain. They both seem to be the same character because of the same name and same blood reference, but this Bartuc could just be a tribute to the Warlord of Blood. This Bartuc could just have acted similar to the Warlord and so earned a similar title.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Legacy of Blood&lt;/a&gt; novel by Knaak (deemed canon by &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;) makes it seem as if it is impossible for the Warlord to come back to &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; without his armour. And since his armour was destroyed by Horazon just before &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; entered &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;, Baal would not have had the armour to resurrect the Warlord of Blood.\nBartuc the Bloody is not wearing armour though, so it is possible that &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; just brought back half of his soul without the half in the armour. It is also possible that only the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt; have the power to do that, while the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Evils\"&gt;Lesser Evils&lt;/a&gt; do not, because &lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt; was interested in reviving the Warlord but needed his armour to do so.\nDevelopment.\nBartuc The Bloody has an unused pale color palette due to Council Member monsters lack of palshift.dat file and randtransform.dat file error in D2Client.dll"}
{"id": "28709", "revid": "44564686", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28709", "title": "Barty the Miniscule", "text": "Barty the Miniscule, Tiny Murderer, is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20One%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen One&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Stinging%20Winds\"&gt;Stinging Winds&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20II%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAs his name suggests, Barty is very small (way smaller than other Fallen), but is surprisingly quick. In combat, he has the Electrified &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Traits%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;affix&lt;/a&gt;, and in addition his melee blows are both quick and deal very heavy damage."}
