{"id": "2673", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2673", "title": "Bash (Diablo II)", "text": "Bash is a &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"The immense physical strength of the Barbarian people is widely known, so it should come as no surprise that this is one of the first skills that they develop as a warrior. Summoning up their renowned brute strength a Barbarian can deliver a powerful and painful blow that staggers an enemy from its feet, knocking them back. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nBash releases a powerful blow that increases damage and knocks the target back. Damage and &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt; are also increased compared to normal blow; damage is added both as flat amount and percentage (after flat increase). All other special effects of the attack, if any, still apply.\nThis skill may be used to knock attackers out of melee range for easier dispatching of multiple foes or to protect an ally that's under heavy assault. Against ranged attackers, however, it serves ill purpose, as most Barbarian attacks are used in close combat.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 2"}
{"id": "9270", "revid": "14250", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9270", "title": "Bash (Diablo III)", "text": "Bash is a Primary skill.\nIn-game.\nHits a single enemy within 6 yards of the Barbarian (a little bit farther than a normal melee blow), essentially an empowered basic attack. Has the highest single-target damage, as well as highest &lt;a href=\"Fury\"&gt;Fury&lt;/a&gt; generated, among all Primary skills.\nFury generation note.\nThe fury is only generated if an enemy is actually hit with the attack: there's no gain if one shift-clicks to attack thin air."}
{"id": "38793", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38793", "title": "Bash (Diablo IV)", "text": "Bash\u00a0is a Basic skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", a variant of the classic &lt;a href=\"Bash\"&gt;Bash&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nIn-game.\nAs previously, Bash is a single-target damage skill with added chance of inflicting Stun. Requires a blunt weapon (&lt;a href=\"Maces\"&gt;Maces&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Maces\"&gt;Two-Handed Maces&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;Staves&lt;/a&gt;) to be equipped and switches to those when used.\nCounts as Berserker skill."}
{"id": "19666", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19666", "title": "Bashanishu", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Bashanishu\"&gt;Bashanishu&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is a Challenge &lt;a href=\"Achievement\"&gt;Achievement&lt;/a&gt; completed by hitting the rare, &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Shaman%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen Shaman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bashiok%20%28Monster%29\"&gt;Bashiok&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0with &lt;a href=\"Rakanishu%27s%20Blade\"&gt;Rakanishu's Blade&lt;/a&gt;. In a cooperative game, it is only granted to players that have directly hit Bashiok with the blade, not all players in the party. Upon completion, a new &lt;a href=\"banner\"&gt;banner&lt;/a&gt; accent will be available.\nThere are two overall steps to completing the achievement: Obtaining the blade, and hitting Bashiok with it. \nObtaining Rakanishu's Blade.\n&lt;a href=\"Rakanishu%27s%20Blade\"&gt;Rakanishu's Blade&lt;/a&gt; is obtained by completing the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Rakanishu\"&gt;Shrine of Rakanishu&lt;/a&gt; event, which does not always appear. This is probably easiest in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;. There are two alternative sub-strategies: Look for the Shrine of Rakanishu &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; appearing on the map and restart the game until it does, or directly looking for the Shrine in the &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; and restart the game until it does.\nOnce the Shrine is found, complete the event and look for the Blade to drop. It is unconfirmed whether its drop rate is 100%. If it doesn't appear, restart the game and try again.\nHitting Bashiok with the blade.\nOnce the blade is found, the primary concerns are finding &lt;a href=\"Bashiok%20%28Monster%29\"&gt;Bashiok&lt;/a&gt;, and ensuring you can hit him with the weapon before he is killed in some other way.\nTo find Bashiok, once again there are two alternative sub-strategies: Look on the map for a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; to kill Bashiok, or search the Oasis for him. In either case, restart the game until successful. Both take a long time, as the bounty is only one among many \"kill bounties\", but Bashiok himself is rare and the Oasis is large. Bashiok is a unique &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Shaman%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen Shaman&lt;/a&gt;, but it is possible for him to appear with other &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; Fallen Shaman in the zone, so most of the zone needs to be covered to be sure.\nOnce he's found, hit him with the basic weapon attack or any other direct attack skill - achievement obtained."}
