{"id": "16311", "revid": "188906", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16311", "title": "Bat (magic suffix)", "text": "Bat is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides a small &lt;a href=\"Mana%20Steal\"&gt;Mana Steal&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 7, but will not be able to spawn on all items until level 35. Some items also are not able to acquire full effect.\nThe steal comes from how much damage you do to the monster. So 5% Mana Stolen will return 5% of the damage you do to a monster. Mana steal only works on melee and physical ranged attacks.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloves\"&gt;Gloves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;Rings&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "3162", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3162", "title": "Bat Demon", "text": "Bat Demons are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nBats are natural inhabitants of caves and other such dank places, so it is no surprise that they would also congregate near the gateways to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;. Their exposure to the vile powers that emanate from the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that frequent these dark places has tainted these bats with &lt;a href=\"arcane\"&gt;arcane&lt;/a&gt; powers. They have also acquired a taste for &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; flesh and fall upon unsuspecting travelers who stray too far from safe passageways. While a single Bat Demon is an annoyance, in swarms, they are lethal, swarming their foes and tearing off mouthfuls of flesh with their sharp teeth.\nIn-game.\nBat Demons can shoot &lt;a href=\"Lightning\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; from their bodies, which actually doesn't always deal lightning damage. Within the game, they are often found in dark, secluded places, such as &lt;a href=\"sewers\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt; and tombs.\nTheir behaviour mimics the animal their name speaks of. They can be a nuisance to deal with because they can cling to the ceiling, out of sight, and although they can be attacked while \"nesting\" a melee character may have to walk a fair distance to attack such a creature. Their shock attack is not too damaging but these maneuverable creatures can be quite destructive.\nWhen using their electric attack, they have a 65/70/75/80/85% chance respectively to deal Lightning damage."}
