{"id": "34837", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34837", "title": "Shrouded Moors", "text": "The Shrouded Moors are an &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", implemented in Patch 2.6.0. They are located in the north of .\nLore.\nThe Shrouded Moors are a harsh, inhospitable land that border a verdant wilderness. Located in &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;, the moors are a rain-swept, windy, and desolate grassland, complete with rocks and plateaus. Fetid swamps stretch further than the eye can see, one's vision obscured by the dense fog that covers the area. Due to the lack of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; activity, one has the eerie sense of being watched in the area. Its primary inhabitants are foul and vicious beasts, which scavenge for any prey they can find.\nHistory.\nThe moors have been occupied by armies and empires over time. Many civilizations have tried to settle here but none ever lasted, their remnants still visible throughout the land. The purpose of these stone structures is lost to time, but stand as the only clue of human settlement in the area. The notion that treasure and glory awaited in the area could tempt even the most cautious individual them, however.\nBy the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, the moors had been abandoned for centuries. But then, something stirred within its perpetual fog, as though a dark presence had taken hold. &lt;a href=\"Monster\"&gt;Monster&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s began to roam the area. &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; received word that the moors might be less deserted than previously thought. Lurking below, a &lt;a href=\"Vidian\"&gt;great evil&lt;/a&gt; had begun to stir, drawing followers with most unsettling desires..."}
