{"id": "2430", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2430", "title": "Shrunken Heads", "text": "Shrunken heads, also known as Voodoo Heads, are the unique &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;s in \"\". They do not offer as much in terms of &lt;a href=\"defense\"&gt;defense&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;s, but they usually have .\nShrunken Heads can have 1-3 bonuses of +1-3 to Necromancer Skill Levels and can only be equipped by Necromancers. You normally hold Shrunken Heads in the &lt;a href=\"off-hand\"&gt;off-hand&lt;/a&gt; slot like shields, together with a &lt;a href=\"Wands\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Daggers\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; or another &lt;a href=\"one-handed\"&gt;one-handed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. You cannot hold two Shrunken Heads at the same time on the same weapon tab.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", some &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mojos\"&gt;Mojos&lt;/a&gt; have the form of shrunken heads, but do not have the shield-like statistics or Necromancer-focused bonuses of the \"Diablo II\" type. &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;s of the later game wield &lt;a href=\"Phylacteries\"&gt;Phylacteries&lt;/a&gt; as their &lt;a href=\"Class-specific%20Items\"&gt;class-specific&lt;/a&gt; off-hand item instead.\nAuto Mods.\n&lt;a href=\"Auto%20Mod\"&gt;Auto Mod&lt;/a&gt;s are mods that \"automatically\" show up on all versions of an item, whether it's magical, normal, damaged, or rare. One Auto Mod from a given group is chosen for the item based on a random number and the level of the item (and the requirements of the Auto Mod). Many Class-specific items contain Auto Mods while others contain spell/skill bonuses.\nNecromancer Shrunken Head Auto Mods\nBlight - 2-7 Poison Damage Over 3 Seconds (1)\nVenom - 5-14 Poison Damage Over 3 Seconds (15)\nPestilence - 13-18 Poison Damage Over 4 Seconds (25)\nAnthrax - 20-50 Poison Damage Over 4 Seconds (33)\nTrivia.\nThe majority of the heads are named after &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in the game, suggesting that they may actually be the severed heads of said monsters."}
