{"id": "44357", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44357", "title": "Shumbeel", "text": "Shumbeel, the Howling Terror was a gigantic manticore-esque &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;. He was one of the greatest servants of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Howling Terror, Shumbeel is a ravenous predator whose shattering screams drove angels to the ground throughout the &lt;a href=\"Battlefields%20of%20Eternity\"&gt;Battlefields of Eternity&lt;/a&gt;. Loosed on &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, it meddles in the tiny movements of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;mortals&lt;/a&gt; not out of care for their strategy, but for the opportunity to watch so many of them scatter at once.\nBiography.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231271\"&gt;1271&lt;/a&gt;, Shumbeel was summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; to free the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;Voidwound&lt;/a&gt;. Before he could finish breaking their cage, he was bound by &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;Nisza&lt;/a&gt;, whose &lt;a href=\"Untameable%20Wilds\"&gt;coven&lt;/a&gt; was responsible for maintaining the seal on the Voidwound. With the help of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, Shumbeel was made to retreat.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;Later&lt;/a&gt;, Shumbeel was again summoned by the Cult of Terror when they besieged &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Keep\"&gt;Stormpoint Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He began harassing the keep's forces, barraging them with &lt;a href=\"lightning\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; blasts, as well as attacking &lt;a href=\"the%20Shanties\"&gt;the Shanties&lt;/a&gt;. Shumbeel was finally summoned to &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Pinnacle\"&gt;the peak&lt;/a&gt; of Stormpoint Keep to fight &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, where he was killed. \nIt is implied that the skin and fur of Shumbeel was used to make armor.\nIn-game.\nShumbeel first appears in \"\"&lt;a href=\"the%20Chainbreakers\"&gt;the Chainbreakers&lt;/a&gt;\"\" &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. He is briefly seen in \" and \"&lt;a href=\"Breaking%20the%20Siege\"&gt;Breaking the Siege&lt;/a&gt;\". He is one of the bosses in \"&lt;a href=\"Bound%20for%20Eternity\"&gt;Bound for Eternity&lt;/a&gt;\"\".\nCombat.\nShumbeel attacks with the following \nIn a cutscene, Shumbeel uses lightning breath on some Stormpoint guards."}
{"id": "43818", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43818", "title": "Shura", "text": "Shura is a &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; stationed at the &lt;a href=\"Sanctified%20Earth%20Monastery\"&gt;Sanctified Earth Monastery&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nShura is a native of Mount Zavain, and grew up in the &lt;a href=\"Sanctified%20Earth%20Monastery\"&gt;Sanctified Earth Monastery&lt;/a&gt; as a disciple of &lt;a href=\"Zaim\"&gt;Zaim&lt;/a&gt;. One of his role models growing up was &lt;a href=\"Patriarchs\"&gt;Patriarch&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sladyan\"&gt;Sladyan&lt;/a&gt;. As a youth, He befriended &lt;a href=\"Oza\"&gt;Oza&lt;/a&gt;, who was transferred from another monastery. \nForgotten Nightmares.\nSometime after &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;'s defeat, &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;Black Mists&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Misty%20Valley\"&gt;Misty Valley&lt;/a&gt; started to spread to other parts of the mountain, and the monastery was almost overrun by &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Nightmares&lt;/a&gt;. Aware of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;'s actions with Oza, who had spoken highly of the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;, Shura sent a &lt;a href=\"Plea%20for%20Help\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;the adventurer's contact&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, asking for help.\nWith the monastery overrun, Shura and the other Monks sought refuge at &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%27s%20Watch\"&gt;Sentinel's Watch&lt;/a&gt;. Though they were grateful, there was tension between the Monks and the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt; because of &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;old hatreds&lt;/a&gt;. After an argument with &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Vereks\"&gt;Captain Vereks&lt;/a&gt; on how to proceed, Shura took a combined force of volunteers to eradicate the source of the mists. During the fighting, some of Shura's fellow Monks were lost to the mists in the &lt;a href=\"Sanctified%20Earth%20Monastery\"&gt;Sanctified Earth Monastery&lt;/a&gt;. \nShura met with the Shard-seeker, and declared his intention to travel to the monastery to use Sladyan's mantra to dispel the mists. Sladyan had used his power to dispel the mists centuries ago, and Shura believed the deed could be repeated. Together, they travelled to the Sanctified Earth Monastery, to Sladyan's statue to reveal the truths of the past and retrieve Sladyan's mantra. The vision revealed details Shura did not expect, and hinted that his idol might be connected to the origin of the mists.\nAt first, he didn't want to believe it but his companion was able to make him see reason. With the mantra they retrieved they discovered the origin of the mists; a &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monastery\"&gt;Veradani temple&lt;/a&gt; that was lost during the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;Zakarum Crusade&lt;/a&gt;. Using the mantra, Shura cleared the mist around the entrance, but could not follow his companion inside, as he had to maintain the mantra that cleared the path.\nAfter some time, the mists slightly receded, and his companion exited the monastery with proof of the mists' source; a corrupted prayer bead that belonged to Patriarch Sladyan. After purifying the bead, the mists further receded but did not completely fade. They discovered that the mists was actually a manifestation of the hatred borne by the people of Zavain, and as long as its people still carried old hatreds in their hearts, it wouldn't completely fade. This made Shura to come to terms with his own grudges and resolve to find peace by letting his hatred go.\nIn-game.\nShura is the &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; companion for the \"&lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;line in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPersonality and Traits.\nShura is a passionate man and cares deeply for those he holds there. This means that he holds deep grudges against those he feels wronged by (ie. &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;Dravec&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;). He is loyal to those he believes in, to the point of denying their faults. Fortunately, he is able to set aside his grudges for the greater good of those he cares about.\nShura is a skilled combatant, showing proficiency with the , &lt;a href=\"Flying%20Kick\"&gt;Flying Kick&lt;/a&gt; and skills. In the &lt;a href=\"World%27s%20Crown\"&gt;World's Crown&lt;/a&gt;, he used &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Rush\"&gt;Tempest Rush&lt;/a&gt; to rampage through a horde of demons. He is also knowledgeable in different mantras."}
