{"id": "9220", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9220", "title": "Silence", "text": "Silence\u00a0was supposed to be a &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; effect in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", but it was cut prior to game's release.\nAs in many other fantasy games, Silence would have prevented the enemy from using &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; spells and active skills for the duration. The reason why this effect has been canceled is unknown: most likely, it proved to be overpowered in PvP. Against monsters, it is of arguable usefulness due to most enemies not using magic in combat.\nOriginally, it was planned that &lt;a href=\"Arcane\"&gt;Arcane&lt;/a&gt; skills would silence enemy on a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe closest equivalent to this effect in other games is &lt;a href=\"Dim%20Vision\"&gt;Dim Vision&lt;/a&gt; that prevents some (but not all!) monsters from using their special skills."}
{"id": "4417", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4417", "title": "Silence Rune Word", "text": "Silence is the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt; \" for &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSilence is an expensive rune word with powerful and diverse attributes, of use to a variety of builds. It is versatile among many classes, and its increased magic find is useful as well.\nSilence was one of the most powerful rune words in version 1.08, and it was the subject to a bug; a Silence with its runes removed via &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; would retain its stats, but allowed for the item to be socketed with additional runes, gems, or jewels. This bug was fixed in later patches. \nWhile Silence is still a powerful rune word, its place among the most powerful rune words is supplanted by rune words introduced in later patches, such as &lt;a href=\"Grief\"&gt;Grief&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Last%20Wish\"&gt;Last Wish&lt;/a&gt;. \nResult:"}
