{"id": "43801", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43801", "title": "Silent Monastery", "text": "The Silent Monastery is a &lt;a href=\"Dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt; update.\nLore.\nThe Silent Monastery is an ancient &lt;a href=\"Sahptev\"&gt;Sahptev&lt;/a&gt; temple.\nHistory.\nZakarum Crusade.\nLong ago, a monastery of Sahptev stood in what is currently the &lt;a href=\"Misty%20Valley\"&gt;Misty Valley&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. Towards the end of the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;Zakarum Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, it was attacked by the &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Light\"&gt;Brotherhood of Light&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 a regiment sect of the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;, who sought to purge the land of &lt;a href=\"Veradani\"&gt;heretics&lt;/a&gt;.\nLed by a &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Martanos\"&gt;ruthless commander&lt;/a&gt;, they slaughtered every inhabitant that they could. Even the &lt;a href=\"Sladyan\"&gt;patriarch&lt;/a&gt; of the monastery was defeated. In a desperate bid to stop the invaders, the the patriarch unleashed an &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Nightmare\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; which was sealed beneath the monastery.\nIts corruption spread in the form of &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;Black Mists&lt;/a&gt;, that killed all the combatants and turned them into &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;. The mists covered the &lt;a href=\"Misty%20Valley\"&gt;surrounding valley&lt;/a&gt;, killing everything and birthing &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;nightmare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. Over time, the monastery at the heart of the mist was forgotten, only tales of the great battle surviving.\nForgotten Nightmares.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231271\"&gt;1271&lt;/a&gt;, foreboding black mist began emanating from the monastery, rolling off the peaks of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; and creeping into &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%27s%20Watch\"&gt;Sentinel's Watch&lt;/a&gt;. The fog threatened to encase the entire area in incomprehensible darkness. A &lt;a href=\"Shura\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt; wrote a &lt;a href=\"Plea%20for%20help\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;(s) asking for help. The Shard-seeker(s) were able to clear the mists.\nGameplay.\nThe Silent Monastery is located a little to the north east of the Misty Valley Waypoint. It is first accessed as part of the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;; \"&lt;a href=\"Seeker%20of%20Truth\"&gt;Seeker of Truth&lt;/a&gt;\". Navigating the monastery allows players to relive the history of the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; crusades through &lt;a href=\"Ivgorod%20%28Country%29\"&gt;Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe inside of the Silent Monastery is home to eternal night, making it nearly impossible to navigate. Fortunately, some of the temple\u2019s statues can be illuminated. Make haste in lighting these statues, they are the only thing that can weaken the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s lurking in the shadows. As players light additional statues and rid the dungeon of monsters, the darkness will be cast out of that area for good."}
