{"id": "9425", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9425", "title": "Singer", "text": "The Singer, Bardarian, or War Crier is a PvM-build, centered around the &lt;a href=\"War%20Cry%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;War Cry&lt;/a&gt; skill. It also serves as supportive caster in multiplayer-games.\nWar Cry.\nWar Cry stuns the enemy and deals moderate physical damage. It costs a lot of Mana, which means that the has to be skilled like a wizardish character. Another possibility is using &lt;a href=\"Insight%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Insight&lt;/a&gt; on your mercenary for &lt;a href=\"Meditation\"&gt;Meditation aura&lt;/a&gt;, for mana regeneration so you can keep your barbarian build.\nStat Point Distribution.\nStrength: Enough to wear endgame gear. Calculate this amount ahead of time.\nDexterity: None. You won't use a shield.\nVitality: Everything that doesn't go into strength.\nEnergy: None. Get your mana from gear and charms.\nSkill Point Distribution.\n&lt;a href=\"War%20Cry%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;War Cry&lt;/a&gt;: Dealing damage. Main attack.\n&lt;a href=\"Battle%20Orders\"&gt;Battle Orders&lt;/a&gt;: Increases your and your party's Life and Mana enormously.\n&lt;a href=\"Shout%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Shout&lt;/a&gt;: Increases your and your party's defense.\nThe rest goes into 1-point-wonders and synergies of War Cry: &lt;a href=\"Taunt%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Taunt&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Cry%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Battle Cry&lt;/a&gt;\n1 point into &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Skin\"&gt;Iron Skin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Natural%20Resistance%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Natural Resistance&lt;/a&gt; will give large defense bonuses with + to skills gear.\nDo NOT invest in any skills like weapons masteries and such. If you have leveling issues in reaching level 30, invest 1 point (more would be waste) in either &lt;a href=\"Bash%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Bash&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Frenzy%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Frenzy&lt;/a&gt;.\nEquipment.\nOn ladder, dual spirit crystal swords is a good starting point. Upgrade to dual HotO's. Add other gear that maximizes +skills while hitting the +105 FCR breakpoint. Look for barb-only helms that add to War Cry and Battle orders (such as &lt;a href=\"Wolfhowl\"&gt;Wolfhowl&lt;/a&gt; Fury Visor). In a 3 socket helm, make a &lt;a href=\"Delirium%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Delirium Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "24848", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24848", "title": "Single Out", "text": "Single Out\u00a0is a passive skill, unlocked at level 68.\nIn-game.\nThis skill is specifically designed for boss fights in general, though it really shines against bosses like &lt;a href=\"Urzael\"&gt;Urzael&lt;/a&gt;, due to the fact that some of those foes prefer to fight alone. This skill may be worth the sacrifice of another passive skill for these cases. For bosses like &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;, which spend most of the fight accompanied by &lt;a href=\"minions\"&gt;minions&lt;/a&gt;, it is slightly less useful, but still one of the most effective abilities.\nOne may also try to use it in tandem with &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Immobilize\"&gt;Immobilize&lt;/a&gt; effects in attempt to separate powerful foes from each other, but it's a far less viable strategy."}
