{"id": "47687", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47687", "title": "Sir Cromwell", "text": "Sir Cromwell was a member of the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20Penitent\"&gt;Knights Penitent&lt;/a&gt;.\nCromwell and his fellow knights were stationed at &lt;a href=\"Kasama\"&gt;Kasama&lt;/a&gt; when their leader, Lord &lt;a href=\"Avitus\"&gt;Avitus&lt;/a&gt;, was slain. Cromwell and his fellow knights carried Avitus's body to the &lt;a href=\"Hallowed%20Ossuary\"&gt;Hallowed Ossuary&lt;/a&gt;, but he arose as a &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;, killing all of them except Cromwell, albeit severely wounding him. Cromwell fled, and was found by , bleeding on the snow. Cromwell told the Wanderer what had happened and asked them to kill Avitus.\nIn-game.\nCromwell is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". He can be found northeast of the eastern entrance of &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;. Talking to him initiates \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Dread%20Martyr\"&gt;The Dread Martyr&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nCromwell's fate is never made explicit, though his opening lines imply that he is fated to die regardless."}
{"id": "8896", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8896", "title": "Sir Gorash", "text": "Sir Gorash was a knight of &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; turned servant of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nThe Darkening of Tristram.\nAs a knight of Khanduras, Gorash was among those &lt;a href=\"King%20Leoric\"&gt;King Leoric&lt;/a&gt; sent to wage war against &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Serving under &lt;a href=\"Lachdanan\"&gt;Lachdanan&lt;/a&gt;, he was also one of the few who managed to return to &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt; after the disastrous campaign. When the knights returned to confront their lord, Leoric lost all pretense of sanity and ordered his guards upon them. Gorash and his fellow knights defended themselves, and the ensuring battle took them into the depths of the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;. Lachdanan was forced to kill his mad liege\u2014in his death cry, Leoric brought down a curse upon his knights, consigning them to eternal damnation.\nThe knights lay him to rest in his burial chamber. As they did so however, Leoric returned to life in the form of a &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;skeletal demon&lt;/a&gt;. Gorash and the other knights were overcome instantly. Rising as a &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Knight\"&gt;Hell Knight&lt;/a&gt;, he resided in &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; itself, in close proximity to Diablo. However, he was slain by a &lt;a href=\"Aidan\"&gt;trio&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jazreth\"&gt;of&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Moreina\"&gt;heroes&lt;/a&gt;.\nMad King's Breach.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;Seven years&lt;/a&gt; after his death, Gorash returned in spectral/&lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; form. However, he was again slain.\nIn-game.\nDiablo I.\nSir Gorash is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Knight\"&gt;Blood Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\" who is found on Dungeon &lt;a href=\"Level%2016%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Level 16&lt;/a&gt;. He is found in proximity to Diablo, and is one of the most powerful Unique Monsters in the game. Because of his color swap he looks nearly like a Steel Lord. \nHis abilities are Charm, &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Curse\"&gt;Stone Curse&lt;/a&gt;, Ignore Walls, Open Doors, Follow and Block Evasion. Unlike normal &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Knight\"&gt;Hell Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, Sir Gorash doesn't have any immunities or resistances, making him vulnerable to various magical attacks.\nDiablo Immortal.\nSir Gorash appears as a &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; boss in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is the first boss of the &lt;a href=\"Mad%20King%27s%20Breach\"&gt;Mad King's Breach&lt;/a&gt;. He has Nightmarish and Waller &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Traits%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;traits&lt;/a&gt;. He also has a slam attack that deals large damage and &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt;. He normally uses Nightmarish to give himself space, and Waller to box in the player before finishing off with the slam attack."}
{"id": "46790", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46790", "title": "Sir Lynna", "text": "Sir Lynna, Disciple of the Dark is &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Super Unique Monster&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Kulsik%20Plateau\"&gt;Kulsik Plateau&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nOnce a promising and devout member of the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20Penitent\"&gt;Knights Penitent&lt;/a&gt;, Lynna turned away from the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; and was declared a heretic. She resided on Kulsik Plateau, where she was killed by .\nIn-game.\nSir Lynna is found in &lt;a href=\"Kulsik%20Plateau\"&gt;Kulsik Plateau&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt;. In a fight, she possesses standard &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Knight\"&gt;Pale Knight&lt;/a&gt; abilities. Additionally, she has Shadow Enchanted affix.\nAfter being defeated, she drops &lt;a href=\"Darkblade%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;Darkblade&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "34374", "revid": "166374", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34374", "title": "Sir William", "text": "Sir William, Happiness Hugs,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cuddle%20Bear\"&gt;Cuddle Bear&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Whimsyshire\"&gt;Whimsyshire&lt;/a&gt; (only Whimsyshire, \"NOT\" in &lt;a href=\"Whimsydale\"&gt;Whimsydale&lt;/a&gt;) in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn combat, he has Desecrator, Molten and Thunderstorm affixes.\nHe has a very low chance of spawning, but if he appears, he is guaranteed to drop a book that will give player a Whimsyshire-themed portrait.\n\"It's like a party on your head!\""}
{"id": "46478", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46478", "title": "Siraj", "text": "Siraj was an Amber Blade guard.\nBiography.\nSiraj was deeply troubled by the scarcity of food his village had been suffering for so long. After the &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt; was reopened, he ventured into it in search of a solution. There, he found info about an elixir that could make a land very fertile. The only problem; it was within a guarded chamber. To continue his research into the seals on the treasure chamber, he laired within a hidden lair.\nAfter a while, an &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; opened a portal to his lair using a portal tome. When Siraj came out to check, he recognized them as the one who convinced &lt;a href=\"Peth\"&gt;Peth&lt;/a&gt; to open the path to Kulle's library. He convinced them to protect him as he retrieves loot from the treasure chamber, and promised a third of the loot. Unfortunately, there was no treasure, only a trap that turned the floor of the whole room into a quicksand vortex. Siraj was unable to escape.\nIn-game.\nSiraj is featured in the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;; \"\"&lt;a href=\"An%20Astounding%20opportunity\"&gt;An Astounding opportunity&lt;/a&gt;\"\". He dies at the end of the quest."}
