{"id": "37457", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37457", "title": "Skarn", "text": "Skarn, the Herald of Terror, was a powerful &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;. He rose from being a minor demon during the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Conflict\"&gt;Eternal Conflict&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s lieutenant by the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;. He is one of the chaos gods of the &lt;a href=\"Sahptev\"&gt;Sahptev&lt;/a&gt; faith as the God of Retribution and Damnation.\nBiography.\nLittle has been recorded of Skarn, despite his high standing in &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;. Skarn was once &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s most powerful lieutenant, though has also been described as a minor demon. He came to develop an interest in humanity, specifically in their so-called \"angelic sin\" (per their &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; heritage).\nEternal Conflict.\nDuring the Eternal Conflict, Skarn was an &lt;a href=\"overseer\"&gt;overseer&lt;/a&gt; in the armies of the Burning Hells. He had fought in many battles, even witnessing the &lt;a href=\"Gates%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Gates of Hell&lt;/a&gt; put under siege by the &lt;a href=\"Angelic%20Host\"&gt;Angelic Host&lt;/a&gt;, and fought under the Lords of Hell as they assault the &lt;a href=\"Diamond%20Gates\"&gt;Diamond Gates&lt;/a&gt;. However, he believed that the war would never end.\nEven then, he was ambitious, and saw himself as a visionary second only to the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Evils\"&gt;Great Evils&lt;/a&gt;.\nDark Exile.\nWith &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;the banishment&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt; from Hell, the realm fell into civil war, as it was split between the followers of &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;. Skarn flourished during this age, but demonologists cannot say whether he led an army, or simply used the conflict as an opportunity to capture parts of the Hells for himself.\nSkarn siphoned power from Diablo's remains (whose spirit he kept bound to prevent him from returning.), and used it to create his own realm in Hell, the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. He ruled his realm from the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Punishment\"&gt;Halls of Punishment&lt;/a&gt;, where he tortured &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s and demons alike.\nThe Power Vacuum.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s defeat at &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn beheld a power vacuum he could take advantage of. If he could obtain just one &lt;a href=\"Worldstone%20shards\"&gt;shard of the Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, he would be able to remove the angelic side of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity, leaving only their demonic half. \nSkarn pulled demons from the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20Anguish\"&gt;Pit of Anguish&lt;/a&gt; to reinforce his armies, as well as using &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Gate\"&gt;Demon Gate&lt;/a&gt;s to summon demons from other parts of the Hells into his realm for the same purpose. In the mortal realm, Skarn gained a massive &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;cult&lt;/a&gt; of followers dedicated to him. Over a period of a few years, they swelled their ranks from recruits taken across the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Kingdoms\"&gt;Western Kingdoms&lt;/a&gt;. Contact with humanity reinforced Skarn's belief that the nephalem had been spoiled by their parentage. Humankind could win the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Conflict\"&gt;Eternal Conflict&lt;/a&gt; for him if only they were purged of their angelic essence.\nImmortal.\nIn the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn rallied a new &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic army, intending to gather the fragments of the corrupted &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;; to reignite the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Conflict\"&gt;Eternal Conflict&lt;/a&gt;, and to bring &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; to its knees.\nSkarn's Cult of Damnation abducted villagers from &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt; for sacrifice. &lt;a href=\"Aelin\"&gt;One villager&lt;/a&gt; made it back to Wortham, but this was possibly intentional, as upon his arrival in the &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn spoke through the villager, mocking those who looked on in horror, before leaving his host's body a charred &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;. Later, in their &lt;a href=\"Unseen%20Lair\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eskara\"&gt;Eskara&lt;/a&gt; and her fellow cultists attempted to summon Skarn into &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, but they were interrupted by &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;. Skarn bid that his followers slay the intruder(s), but they failed, and the summoning was averted. \nLater, in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn spoke through one of his &lt;a href=\"Damned%20Cultist\"&gt;cultists&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Lakrii\"&gt;Lakrii&lt;/a&gt;, leader of the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;. He demanded that he deliver the Worldstone fragment that had fallen in the forest, and in return, he would give her whatever her heart desired. Otherwise, the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; would cleanse &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. Lakrii responded that the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone%20shards\"&gt;shard&lt;/a&gt; was in the possession of &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the one&lt;/a&gt; whose heart she desired, and besides, if Skarn had the power to scour Sanctuary, he'd be taking the stone, not asking for it. Lakrii slew Skarn's vessel.\nFall of Damnation.\nSkarn succeeded in getting a shard from &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;a Monk&lt;/a&gt;. He then turned him into &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Souls\"&gt;a demon&lt;/a&gt; and retreated to &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;his domain&lt;/a&gt; where he would attune the shard to himself. Once the Shard-seeker followed him to Hell, with his control over the domain he began corrupting them, but they were saved by &lt;a href=\"Yl%27nira\"&gt;an angelic dagger&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Shard-seeker found his &lt;a href=\"Pits%20of%20Anguish\"&gt;demon pits&lt;/a&gt;, where Skarn creates his demonic legion using the stolen Light of angels. The heroes destroyed almost all of them using Yl'nira. Unknown to them, Yl'nira gained a little bit of corruption with each pit destroyed. By the time they attempted to destroy the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20Anguish\"&gt;last pit&lt;/a&gt;, the dagger was corrupted enough for Skarn to safely steal the dagger and corrupt it. \nThe corrupted Yl'nira was enough to power the last pit that it created a &lt;a href=\"Zaka\"&gt;collosal worm like demon&lt;/a&gt;. Alas, it was killed by the heroes when they went to destroy the last pit from within.\nWith the help &lt;a href=\"Verathiel\"&gt;of&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mikayel\"&gt;some&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Andalon\"&gt;angels&lt;/a&gt;, the Shard-seeker were able to breach Skarn's throne room where they battled and killed him.\nAfter Skarn was killed, his soul was trapped in the Worldstone shard and when the shard was shattered with a corrupted Yl'nira, his spirit was released.\nChained Damnation.\nAfter Skarn's spirit returned to Hell, it was captured by Diablo. Diablo would later call upon Skarn's bound spirit to aid him when fighting the Shard-seeker.\nDawn of Damnation.\n\"Note: The following events are exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt; beta. The timing\u2014and validity, of them is unclear.\"\nSkarn led his forces of Hell against &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; directly, wrecking havoc against &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Only the &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;capital&lt;/a&gt; was able to halt his advance. Enraged, an apparition of Skarn appeared before the Shard-seeker and Westmarch's defenders, promising to unleash Hell upon Sanctuary until they begged for his salvation. The Shard-seeker was dispatched to hunt down his forces.\nIn-game.\nSkarn is one of the central antagonists of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is the final &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; of the baseline game, fought in the Realm of Damnation.\nSkarn doesn't use melee attacks. His attacks are similar to some skills from the and classes:\nPersonality and Traits.\nCruel, calculating and smart, Skarn sees himself as a visionary. Unlike most demons, he doesn't wish the destruction of the heavens and end of the Eternal Conflict. Instead he seeks to despoil and corrupt the angels in every manner, to twist them, until they become the very thing which they hate.\nWith the discovery of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity, Skarn took interest in them and their so-called \"&lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;ic sin.\" He saw humans as being \"true kin\" to demons, neglected, and that only through &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, could mankind find salvation. He extended similar views to the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, considering them to be \"spoiled\" by their angelic heritage. Ergo, humanity could serve him (a view not dissimilar to the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;), but only if the angelic side of their heritage was removed.\nDespite his high standing, Skarn was a somewhat obscure demon\u2014few demonologists even knew his name."}
{"id": "50017", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50017", "title": "Skarn's Throne", "text": " is &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;'s seat of power in the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\n is located within the &lt;a href=\"Citadel%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Citadel of the Damned&lt;/a&gt;, beyond the &lt;a href=\"Molten%20Egress\"&gt;Molten Egress&lt;/a&gt;. It is protected by a gate which would take an &lt;a href=\"archangel\"&gt;archangel&lt;/a&gt;'s weapon or the full strength and dedicated effort of three &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s to breach. A throne made from &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s skull resides within . When Skarn sits on it, he can absorb power from the bound &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; of the Prime Evil.\nRecent History.\nIn the year &lt;a href=\"timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn obtained a shard of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;one&lt;/a&gt; of his worshippers. He then retreated to his throne room to attune the shard to himself. He was pursued by &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; and they fought in after which Skarn was killed. With Skarn's &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, Diablo's &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; was free to return from the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Abyss\"&gt;Black Abyss&lt;/a&gt; and began reforming in the throne room of his traitorous lieutenant.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;Two years later&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;an agent&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; breached , and delivered a large shard of the Worldstone to Diablo.\nIn-game.\n is a Realm of Damnation zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is here that Skarn is fought at the end of the base game. It is also revisited in the \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Rebirth\"&gt;Dark Rebirth&lt;/a&gt;\" update, when the &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Bride of Hell&lt;/a&gt; gives Diablo a Worldstone shard."}
