{"id": "3085", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3085", "title": "Skeleton Archer", "text": "Skeleton Archers are &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; warriors who wield &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt; and fire &lt;a href=\"Arrows\"&gt;Arrows&lt;/a&gt; at their enemies.\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s do not seek to consume the flesh of the living as do many of their other &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; kindred, but seek only to slay those who live to increase their ranks. Single-minded in their mission to slay the living, some of these animated warriors use the bows that served them in life to deadly effect. Archers let their brethren rush forward, while they hang back and fire into the melee.\nIn-game.\nSkeleton Archers appear in all three of the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;\"Diablo\"&lt;/a&gt; games, as ranged variants of their skeleton brethren.\nDiablo I.\nSkeleton Archers appear particularly in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo_I_Walkthrough%23The_Cathedral\"&gt;Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; (Dungeon). They can be quite dangerous in large groups, if not dispatched quickly.\nLike Skeletons, Skeleton Archers have four variants, including Corpse Bows, Burning Dead Archers, and Horror Archers.\nDiablo II.\nSkeleton Archers return in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". They appear often in large packs, and they can be quite deadly; on higher difficulties, only a few volleys are enough to kill even the sturdiest of warriors. They can be found normally with other monsters and act as suppressive fire until the melee units get close enough. A good tactic to deal with Skeleton Archer groups is to lure their melee comrades away until out of range, then deal with the Archers. Since the Skeleton Archers can deal devastating damage in groups, a good way to kill them is to use ranged spells or anything that can do an area-of-effect such as . There are four other variations besides normal Skeleton Archers: Returned Archers, Bone Warrior Archers, Burning Dead Archers, and Horror Archers.\nDiablo Immortal.\nSkeleton Archers appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". A sub-type includes the \"Guardian Archer.\"\nDiablo III.\nSkeleton Archers return in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nA humanoid skeleton with a bow and a relatively slow firing rate, they are not dangerous one on one, but a pack of them can be pretty nasty, especially against low armor or stationary targets. In Diablo III, they usually spawn with &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Shieldman\"&gt;Skeletal Shieldmen&lt;/a&gt;, firing from the relative safety they find behind their blocking brethren. They may also appear with a &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Summoner\"&gt;Skeletal Summoner&lt;/a&gt;. In , they are replaced with &lt;a href=\"Revenant%20Archer\"&gt;Revenant Archer&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Archer\"&gt;Summoned Archer&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0(some Champion Skeletal Archers could be found in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0prior to patch 2.2.0).\nSkeleton Archers may be summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Mage%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Skeleton Mage&lt;/a&gt; skill of the , if equipped with the Skeleton Archer &lt;a href=\"skill%20rune\"&gt;skill rune&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo IV.\nSkeleton Archers appear as enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "40242", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40242", "title": "Skeleton Archer (Guest)", "text": "This is a page for &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty exclusive &lt;a href=\"Guest%20Monsters\"&gt;Guest&lt;/a&gt; variations of &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Archer\"&gt;Skeleton Archers&lt;/a&gt;. \nAll Guest Skeleton Archers are very much like the normal types apart of higher statistics and always shooting elemental arrows."}
{"id": "39545", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39545", "title": "Skeleton Ballista", "text": "The Skeleton Ballista is a type of &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is an amalgamation of skeletons that have come together to barely hold out this giant bow that can fire from multiple screens away."}
