{"id": "41395", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41395", "title": "Skeleton Lord", "text": "The Skeleton Lord is a creature made of fused skeleton and body parts, with sinew and &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; connecting it together. It is a master of &lt;a href=\"necromancy\"&gt;necromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Skeleton Lord is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", apparently as a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;. He summons &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s and bone walls, while leveraging a giant staff that impacts the ground, creating a shower of exploding bone shards that blind the player.\nDevelopment.\nThe Skeleton Lord was conceived as art first, with the design team subsequently using the art as inspiration for his fight. At &lt;a href=\"BlizzCon%202019\"&gt;BlizzCon 2019&lt;/a&gt;, it was called the \"Tomb Lord.\""}
{"id": "3084", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3084", "title": "Skeleton Mage", "text": "Skeleton Mages (a.k.a. Skeletal Mages or Returned Mages) are &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s that utilize &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nSkeleton Mages are the animated remains of slain &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s. They wield the forces of &lt;a href=\"elemental%20magic\"&gt;elemental magic&lt;/a&gt; as they sow death throughout the land. Able to deliver considerable damage from a distance, these &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s can be exceptionally dangerous when congregating in large pacts or under the direction of the remains of a particularly powerful caster. Skeleton Mages sometimes lead groups of other skeletons, but in truth, they're no more intelligent than any normal skeleton\u2014it is only their ability to wield magic that distinguish them.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Priests%20of%20Rathma\"&gt;Priests of Rathma&lt;/a&gt; are likewise able to summon Skeleton Mages from the corpses of long dead &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s. The priests feel that this is the proof of the dominance of their &lt;a href=\"necromancy\"&gt;particular branch&lt;/a&gt; of the mystic arts.\nAt least some Skeletal Mages are capable of speech.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nSkeleton Mages first appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". They attack their enemies by shooting elemental energies from their hands. Skeleton Mages can only wield one type of elemental magic: &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"cold\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;. By looking at glow of their hands, one can tell which element they wield.\nSkeleton Mages are first found in the latter part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt;. Like with &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Archer\"&gt;Skeleton Archer&lt;/a&gt;s, mages are most deadly when they appear in large groups. Maximizing &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt; will greatly decrease damage taken from their attacks. Skeleton Mages themselves do not appear as enemies. However, four variations exist: Returned Mages, Bone Mages, Burning Dead Mages, and Horror Mages. With the exception of Burning Dead Mages, each Skeleton Mage has four different variations: Fire, Cold, Lightning, and Poison. \nBurning Dead Mages have no Cold variation, because they were repurposed as Death Mages of &lt;a href=\"Achmel%20the%20Cursed\"&gt;Achmel&lt;/a&gt;. Returned and Bone Mages wielding Cold and Poison elements aren't used anywhere.\ns can raise their own magical skeletons via the &lt;a href=\"Raise%20Skeletal%20Mage\"&gt;Raise Skeletal Mage&lt;/a&gt; ability.\nDiablo Immortal.\nA &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Mage%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Skeletal Mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLesser skeletons also appear as Mage enemies, but are likewise referred to as \"Skeletal Mages\" or \"Returned Mages.\"\nDiablo III.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Guardian\"&gt;Skeletal Guardian&lt;/a&gt; takes on a similar role as the Skeletal Mage. s retain the &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Mage%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Skeletal Mage&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nDevelopment.\nSkeleton Mages in Diablo II have four casting sounds titled firemage, castice, castelectric, castpoison.wav but all of them use only firemage.wav.\nIn v1.00 a &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; Burning Dead Mage could be seen near &lt;a href=\"Radament\"&gt;Radament&lt;/a&gt;, however it was replaced by a Cold Horror Mage in the as the Cold Burning Dead Mage has been repurposed into Death Mage of &lt;a href=\"Achmel%20the%20Cursed\"&gt;Achmel The Cursed&lt;/a&gt;."}
