{"id": "40253", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40253", "title": "Skeleton Mage (Guest)", "text": "This is a page for &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty exclusive &lt;a href=\"Guest%20Monsters\"&gt;Guest&lt;/a&gt; variations of &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Mage\"&gt;Skeleton Mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll Guest Skeleton Mages are like normal skeleton mages apart of: having a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; immunity (not including the Poison-based ones which actually don't have an immunity), higher resistances and a bit faster walking speed than the last variants of normal skeleton mages. What sets both Guest &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Damage%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; mages apart of the normal variants is their projectile that travels much faster.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; Bone Mages are the most common Guest monster and are pretty much guaranteed to appear at least once in a playthrough of &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28Act%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second Poison Horror Mages are the first of two Skeleton Mages in the game that use normal skeleton color palette, the other are the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Mage%20%28Pandemonium%20Event%29\"&gt;Pandemonium Poison Horror Mages&lt;/a&gt;."}
