{"id": "6789", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6789", "title": "Skewer of Krintiz", "text": "Skewer of Krintiz is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; , from \"\".\nAt first, the Skewer of Krintiz' stats may seem lackluster. However, it does indeed have some useful bonuses, most notable is its ability to ignore the target's &lt;a href=\"Defense\"&gt;Defense&lt;/a&gt;. This makes the user much more likely to hit an opponent. This does not necessarily mean that a character will always hit its target, but it will increase their chances quite a bit, especially due to its fair boost to &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, and therefore &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt;.\nCompounding on this ability, the Skewer of Krintiz also gives its user &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt; leech; which is much more effective, since the Skewer of Krintiz generally hits often. &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;Characters&lt;/a&gt; who have combat skills that require mana, yet rarely have a large amount of &lt;a href=\"Energy\"&gt;Energy&lt;/a&gt;, would certainly find this mana leech more useful.\nDespite these bonuses, the Skewer is still a low-level item, and the damage it dishes out is simply too low compared to most unique &lt;a href=\"Exceptional%20Items\"&gt;exceptional&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt;, or even high level &lt;a href=\"Normal%20Items\"&gt;Normal Items&lt;/a&gt;. Perhaps useful in the early Acts of &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, the Skewer of Krintiz is not often used later in game.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 7 To 19 \nRequired Level: 10\nRequired Strength: 25\nRequired Dexterity: 25\nDurability: 32\nSword Class - "}
{"id": "28121", "revid": "26096179", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28121", "title": "Skill", "text": "A Skill is a special ability usable by a player character (or sometimes even a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;) in-game. In the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo series&lt;/a&gt;\", all &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; have distinct unique skills, and (in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;first game&lt;/a&gt;), a shared library of spells. In the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;second&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;third&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;fourth&lt;/a&gt; games, \"all\" skills are class-specific.\nThe total number of skills a character may possess is usually limited, however, usually they may improve their chosen skills by various means. The exact mechanics depend on the game which they are presented in."}
{"id": "16221", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16221", "title": "Skill (magic suffix)", "text": "Skill is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides a small bonus to &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 11, but will not be able to spawn on all items with full effect until level 34.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;Crossbows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloves\"&gt;Gloves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rings\"&gt;Rings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Body%20Armor\"&gt;Body Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Boots\"&gt;Boots&lt;/a&gt;"}
