{"id": "42019", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42019", "title": "Skorspine the Marrowrot", "text": "Skorspine the Marrowrot was a giant &lt;a href=\"scorpion\"&gt;scorpion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20of%20the%20Scorpion\"&gt;Prison of the Scorpion&lt;/a&gt;. Its bones provided the creature with unnatural strength and flexibility.\nIn-game.\nSkorspine is a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Fahir%27s%20Legacy\"&gt;Fahir's Legacy&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nIn the first phase, Skorspine attacks with pincer &lt;a href=\"strike\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt;s, dual-pincered &lt;a href=\"swipe\"&gt;swipe&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"dash\"&gt;dash&lt;/a&gt; attacks. The latter 2 attacks cause &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt;. \nAt total &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, Skorspine creates a field of &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; gas around the arena. It frequently retreats, summoning &lt;a href=\"Vile%20Stinger\"&gt;Vile Stinger&lt;/a&gt;s to attack the player. Skorspine attacks by &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Spray\"&gt;spraying a cone of poison&lt;/a&gt;, or ing the player with its tail. The latter attack leaves toxic pools that persist till Skorspine is killed.\nIt drops &lt;a href=\"Skorspine%27s%20Wrath\"&gt;Skorspine's Wrath&lt;/a&gt; when defeated."}
{"id": "23618", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23618", "title": "Skovos", "text": ""}
{"id": "48700", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48700", "title": "Skovos Isle", "text": ""}
{"id": "3574", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3574", "title": "Skovos Isles", "text": "The Skovos Isles (a.k.a. Amazon Islands) are a group of islands located in the &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Seas\"&gt;Twin Seas&lt;/a&gt;. They consist of four main islands: Philios, Skovos, Lycander, Skartara, and are the home of the &lt;a href=\"Askari\"&gt;Askari&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nSkovos is the main island of the chain, while Philios, Lycander, and Skartara are outlying islands.\nThe isles possess a dense rain-forest environment that teems with life. It is in the forest canopy in which the Askari have constructed their cities. The canopy is so dense that little light reaches the ground. Hunting through the forests' undergrowth is fraught with many obstacles; confining overgrowth and fierce indigenous animals conspire to make combat difficult, if not impossible, though the Amazons have adapted to their forest home in this regard. Some of the native flora is toxic.\nFor the most part, the islands possess an ever-balmy climate, and winter never seems to arrive. \nA number of wars were fought in Skovos in ages past. They have their own trading language.\nTrivia.\nCut Location.\nSkovos was originally intended to appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", but was cut as it didn't seem to fit in. Another issue is that the visuals of Skovos were reminiscent of \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//titanquest.fandom.com/wiki/Titan_Quest\"&gt;Titan Quest&lt;/a&gt;\". At the time the developers were deciding whether to cut Skovos or not, \"Titan Quest\" was the most recent isometric ARPG. Visually, it felt too similar, and it was felt that there were better opportunities elsewhere (in terms of location). However, &lt;a href=\"Wyatt%20Cheng\"&gt;Wyatt Cheng&lt;/a&gt; has expressed hopes that the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;franchise&lt;/a&gt; will revisit Skovos one day.\nIt was revealed during the 2008 &lt;a href=\"BlizzCon\"&gt;BlizzCon&lt;/a&gt;'s Lore &amp; Art Panel for \"Diablo III\" that Skovos would not be accessible to the player during the events of the game, but was internally fleshed out so it could be referenced by the characters in the game world. The isles receive mention in , as &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath Nahr&lt;/a&gt; discuss that a &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; expedition sent to the isles has not returned."}
{"id": "32105", "revid": "3551649", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32105", "title": "Skular", "text": "Skular is a Barbarian warrior, one of the few who managed to survive the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Siege of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; and retain their sanity.\nBiography.\nSkular was present when &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; attacked &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;, and fought to protect the city, chronicling the battle as the events unfolded. When &lt;a href=\"Kanai\"&gt;Kanai&lt;/a&gt; died, and the battle was lost, Skular and other survivors took shelter in the ruins.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;'s destruction, Skular and his brethren hunted down most of &lt;a href=\"the%20Unclean\"&gt;the Unclean&lt;/a&gt; and left the city.\nThey returned later to finish the task and liberate the ruins of both cannibals and vermin, but &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; captured them, only for Skular to be rescued by &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; soon afterwards.\nIn-game.\nPlayers may find Skular in &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is locked in a final cage during the &lt;a href=\"Last%20of%20the%20Barbarians%20%28Event%29\"&gt;Last of the Barbarians&lt;/a&gt; . He then joins the Nephalem, fighting on their side as long as they both remain in the Ruins.\nIn battle, he uses the &lt;a href=\"Cleave\"&gt;Cleave&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Abd%20al-Hazir\"&gt;Abd al-Hazir&lt;/a&gt; is rescued while Skular is following the Nephalem, the barbarian will ask to put the scholar back in the cage for his gossiping. He will comment on other events in the Ruins as well. His dialogue lines change if the player character is a .\nIf taken to the &lt;a href=\"Immortal%20Throne\"&gt;Immortal Throne&lt;/a&gt;, he will say that he must return to his vigil, kneel before &lt;a href=\"Kanai\"&gt;Kanai&lt;/a&gt; and remain there.\n&lt;a href=\"Skular%27s%20Salvation\"&gt;Skular's Salvation&lt;/a&gt; bracers can be found in-game, stating that this item helped him survive the invasion of Baal."}
{"id": "33138", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33138", "title": "Skular's Salvation", "text": "Skular's Salvation\u00a0are\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0bracers in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", added in Patch 2.4.0.\nThe unique affix empowers (with Boulder Toss rune only), and multiplicatively enhances its damage even further if it hits less than 5 enemies."}
