{"id": "21320", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21320", "title": "Skywarden", "text": "The Skywarden is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Maces\"&gt;two-handed mace&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 29 to drop. The &lt;a href=\"Angel\"&gt;angelic&lt;/a&gt; warriors in can be seen wielding such weapons.\nThe special affix grants a random Law (that is, unmodified &lt;a href=\"Crusader\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt; skill, without rune or active effect: &lt;a href=\"Laws%20of%20Valor\"&gt;Laws of Valor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Laws%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Laws of Hope&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Laws%20of%20Justice\"&gt;Laws of Justice&lt;/a&gt;) every 60 seconds. However, the &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; resets if the Crusader dies, changes zones, equips or unequips the weapon.\nIf the Skywarden is equipped by a Crusader who already has a Law on their skill bar, it\u00a0\"may\" grant two Laws at a time. Similar Laws will not stack, however."}
{"id": "43796", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43796", "title": "Sladyan", "text": "Sladyan was a patriarch of a &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monastery\"&gt;monastery&lt;/a&gt; located at &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAs Patriarch of &lt;a href=\"Balance%20%28Philosophy%29\"&gt;Balance&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Sahptev\"&gt;Sahptev&lt;/a&gt; faith, Sladyan the Unbent symbolized harmony between chaos and order, worship and statecraft. When Rakkis's crusade reached &lt;a href=\"Ivgorod\"&gt;Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt;, Sladyan came to symbolize victory. By expelling his &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; with a forbidden technique, Sladyan blanketed Zavain in darkness that would shield and torment his home for centuries.\nZakarum Crusade.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;Zakarum Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, they battled against the &lt;a href=\"Monks%20of%20Ivgorod\"&gt;Monks of Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Light\"&gt;regiment sect&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;, led by &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Martanos\"&gt;Lord Martanos&lt;/a&gt;, was tasked with clearing &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; of heretics. The monastery Sladyan led also came under attack. After being defeated by a Martanos \u2014 who by then had fallen prey to corrupt power, Sladyan trapped him on a peak by breaking the bridge connecting it to the rest of the monastery.\nUnleashed Nightmare.\nIn his desperation to save his home from being overwhelmed, Sladyan used a forbidden ritual to expel his soul from his body. In doing so, his body became a suitable vessel for a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;long-sealed darkness&lt;/a&gt; to inhabit; forming &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Nightmare\"&gt;a new demon&lt;/a&gt; in the process. Corruption spread out as a dark mist that turned all the warriors (both the &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s) to &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nForgotten Nightmares.\nSladyan's &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; still persisted within the Ancient Nightmare, but was continually tormented by it.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231271\"&gt;1271&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;(s) was/were investigating the source of the mists spreading throughout Mount Zavain. They discovered the Silent Monastery and the Ancient Nightmare that laired within it. When fighting the Nightmare, it tried to consume them with &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;Black Mists&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithin the Nightmare's soulscape, they saw Sladyan's tormented soul. Unfortunately, he had already been corrupted and transformed into a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;, forcing them to slay him.\nIn-game.\nSladyan appears in the quest &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt;. In the second phase of battling the Ancient Nightmare, the players are transported to a nightmare realm where they battle a corrupted Sladyan. He uses the following attacks:\nSladyan opens the battle with a slam. He is almost constantly covered with a &lt;a href=\"shadow\"&gt;shadow&lt;/a&gt; based &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20Zen\"&gt;Shield of Zen&lt;/a&gt; which makes him invulnerable, and he frequently summons &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;s to attack. Activating any of the &lt;a href=\"Ytar%27s%20flame\"&gt;Ytar's flame&lt;/a&gt;s temporarily disables his shield, and &lt;a href=\"stun\"&gt;stun&lt;/a&gt;s him and his minions. Sladyan dies after all the flames are activated, after which the player(s) are transported back to fight the Ancient Nightmare."}
{"id": "44929", "revid": "51979909", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44929", "title": "Sladyan's Writings", "text": " is a scroll containing the teachings of &lt;a href=\"Patriarch\"&gt;Patriarch&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sladyan\"&gt;Sladyan&lt;/a&gt; on sanctification. It is featured in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;Diablo Immortal Side Quests&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20Are%20Broken%20Light\"&gt;Shadows Are Broken Light&lt;/a&gt;\", where &lt;a href=\"Elod\"&gt;Elod&lt;/a&gt; shows it to an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;.\nContent.\n\"On Sanctification\nWhen we were blind to our unity, when we forgot our purpose and closed our hearts to one another, I allowed those in my monastery to separate their offerings to the gods of Chaos and Order. They infused the likeness of each with prayer and ablution for months, and spoke only of \"their\" gods, and our halls became further divided.\nThen, I instructed them to draw out the power of their offerings, and bind them together as one in sanctity, until all they invested could no longer be separated, or drawn upon by one faction alone and harmony rang clear like a bell.\""}
