{"id": "17401", "revid": "27010889", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17401", "title": "Slaughtered Calf Inn", "text": "The Slaughtered Calf Inn is a location found in &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is run by &lt;a href=\"Bron%20the%20Barkeep\"&gt;Bron the Barkeep&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn-game.\nDuring the beginning of the game, &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;Leah&lt;/a&gt; can be found here. She lives in a room of the inn that can be entered, rather than one in &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20House\"&gt;Cain's House&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the player first talks to Leah, the sick people that are standing in the Inn will turn into &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Risen Dead&lt;/a&gt; that the player has to defeat.\nWalking into Leah's room will give the player the &lt;a href=\"Visit%20Somewhere%20Nice\"&gt;Visit Somewhere Nice&lt;/a&gt; achievement."}
{"id": "20650", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20650", "title": "Slave Bonds", "text": "Slave Bonds were &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"bracers\"&gt;bracers&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They required &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 29 to drop. In patch 2.2.0, they were replaced with &lt;a href=\"Mortick%27s%20Brace\"&gt;Mortick's Brace&lt;/a&gt;.\nThese bracers were among the few items that could provide a &lt;a href=\"movement%20speed\"&gt;movement speed&lt;/a&gt; boost, and had 5 Primary affixes."}
{"id": "34779", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34779", "title": "Slavut", "text": "Slavut was a priest-turned bandit.\nBiography.\nAt some point Slavut was a priest. However, he abandoned the priesthood, and came to lead a group of people within &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt;, whose village had been overtaken by the desert. They searched for a new place to settle, or a weak village that they could seize. While scouting, came across &lt;a href=\"Lidra\"&gt;Lidra&lt;/a&gt; at a destroyed wagon. He told her that he was once a priest, that he had slain a man who killed his son. Such an act was frowned on by the priesthood. She could tell he was lying about his son, but told him that she was after a &lt;a href=\"Rigley\"&gt;man&lt;/a&gt; who had destroyed the wagon. Slavut was dubious as to her story, and unmoved by her pleas for his aid. All he could tell her was that his camp was due east, about half a day's walk away.\nSlavut turned his back to her, and was rewarded with a knife through his lung. He fell into the sand, dying quickly."}
{"id": "54648", "revid": "46404728", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54648", "title": "Slay Ride to Hell", "text": "Slay Ride to Hell was a Christmas-themed event for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It launched on December 17, 2024 and lasted until January 2, 2025. It had event-exclusive cosmetics and in-game rewards.\nGameplay.\nDuring the event, &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Goblin\"&gt;Treasure Goblin&lt;/a&gt; spawns were greatly increased and the entire \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" community was tasked with slaying Treasure Goblins in order to reach milestone goals. The community had to defeat a total of 40,000,000 Treasure Goblins to unlock the full five tiers of rewards. Once a milestone was reached, the rewards (which included bags containing Ancestral legendary items, gold, and \"&lt;a href=\"Vessel%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Vessel of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;\" currencies) could be claimed from the &lt;a href=\"Midwinter%20Ward\"&gt;Midwinter Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Midwinter%20Square\"&gt;Midwinter Square&lt;/a&gt; was re-purposed for this event with interactable lore pieces describing the rewards such as Pale Marks and Undercity Tributes. The &lt;a href=\"Gifts%20of%20Midwinter\"&gt;Gifts of Midwinter&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic mount set was unlocked for all players to claim out of the in-game shop once the milestones for tiers 3, 4, and 5 were achieved.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Midwinter%20Blight\"&gt;Midwinter Blight&lt;/a&gt;, 2023's Christmas-themed event"}
