{"id": "37587", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37587", "title": "Segithis", "text": "Segithis the Clusterflesh was a servant of &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nWhen one of Fahir's rivals rose against him, he took her brother as his ward. Fahir spent years tinkering at the flesh of his servant, reshaping the body of the boy who once hid from him in the palace. After rebellion toppled Fahir's empire, he bade the spiderlike being follow into &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;his tomb&lt;/a&gt;, offering him the place in eternity his family had sought.\nSegithis was responsible for killing many intruders and of note; &lt;a href=\"Rani%20Oran\"&gt;Rani Oran&lt;/a&gt;'s husband when the two entered the tomb (at the least, her husband's wedding ring ended up in Segithis's possession).\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; entered Fahir's tomb, successfully striking down the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; king. At Fahir's command, Segithis bound him in web and wisked him away to safety. Segithis was later killed, but told his foe(s) that Fahir was now beyond their reach. Searching the area, the Shard-seeker couldn't find Fahir's remains anywhere.\nIn-game.\nSegithis appears as a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", inside the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Tomb of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn the first phase of the fight, Segithis isn't attacked directly, but rather, his legs are, each effectively its own '&lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;.' They down, dealing damage. During this phase, Segithis has an area-of-effect attack, &lt;a href=\"sweep\"&gt;sweep&lt;/a&gt;ing one of his arms horizontally. There is a visual indicator as to where the strike will land beforehand. He also shoots out &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bolt\"&gt;Poison Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s. At the end of each phase, Segithis can be attacked directly, before the legs prop him up again.\nIn the second phase, spider web projectiles will be set out. It can also &lt;a href=\"Spin%20Web\"&gt;Spin Web&lt;/a&gt;s at the player, &lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;slow&lt;/a&gt;ing their movement once it's tethered to them.\nIn the third phase, Segithis is attacked directly.\nDevelopment.\nDuring development, Segithis was referred to as \"&lt;a href=\"Broodmother\"&gt;Broodmother&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
