{"id": "3416", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3416", "title": "Seismic Slam", "text": "Seismic Slam is a Secondary skill, and one of the three that may be described as ranged skills.\nIn-game.\nThe Barbarian lifts up one foot and brings it down with his/her weapon, slamming them into the ground and sending forth a deadly shockwave. This wave expands in a cone, roughly 30 degrees wide and 50 yards long, moving quickly (but not instantly), expanding as it nears its full length.\nThe wave has a minimum width (10 yards) at close distance, and ignores line of sight and most obstacles, including &lt;a href=\"Waller\"&gt;Waller&lt;/a&gt; affix barriers.\nDevelopment.\nSeismic Slam was one of the more difficult skills to develop, as it was the first effects-heavy ability, and involved ground effects. Originally, the terrain would break apart after it was used.\n&lt;a href=\"Upheaval\"&gt;Upheaval&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" fills the same fantasy niche."}
{"id": "30629", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30629", "title": "Seismic Treads", "text": "Seismic Treads were &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boots\"&gt;boots&lt;/a&gt; to be implemented in patch 2.2.0 of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They would require &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 to use.\nPrior to release, they were removed, and their unique affix has been moved to &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Iron\"&gt;Dread Iron&lt;/a&gt;. The graphic was later used for &lt;a href=\"Foundation%20of%20the%20Earth\"&gt;Foundation of the Earth&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "24673", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24673", "title": "Seize the Initiative", "text": "Seize the Initiative\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0passive skill, unlocked at level 20.\nDevelopment.\nPrior to patch 2.1, this skill used to increase\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Defense\"&gt;Armor&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0by 30-50% of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0As in patch 2.1, Armor is increased by Dexterity anyway, so the skill was changed to be more offense-oriented."}
