{"id": "50127", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50127", "title": "Seneschal", "text": "The Seneschal was a robotic &lt;a href=\"pet\"&gt;pet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", available in \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Construct\"&gt;Season of the Construct&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Seneschal was created by &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. It is a mighty weapon, capable of harnessing ancient power for the one strong enough to control it. A one-of-a-kind &lt;a href=\"construct\"&gt;construct&lt;/a&gt;, it was built to command the other constructs, and protect the one commanding it in turn.\nThe Seneschal was buried in a deep below the sands of &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt;. The vault it was buried in was equipped with a number of traps, and a number of &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s lost their lives in pursuit of the device. They emerged from the vault, but the Seneschal was left behind, broken. It was later retrieved by and repaired by &lt;a href=\"Ayuzhan\"&gt;Ayuzhan&lt;/a&gt;, so it would follow the Wanderer's orders.\nGameplay.\nThe Seneschal had various powers that it could be upgraded with. It could buff the player, provide defensive protection or deal damage. The Seneschal itself could not die, and did not have its skills manually activated. The Seneschal could be upgraded with &lt;a href=\"tuning%20stone\"&gt;turning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"governing%20stone\"&gt;governing stone&lt;/a&gt;s and the player could combine effects.\nThe Seneschal's stats scaled with the player's. However, the Seneschal did not proc legendary/paragon/etc. passive effects. \nDevelopment.\nThe Seneschal became so powerful in testing the developers had to buff al &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; in some instances."}
