{"id": "49722", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49722", "title": "Sentinel's Stand", "text": "Sentinel's Stand is the &lt;a href=\"Zone%20Trial\"&gt;Zone Trial&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Dreadlands\"&gt;Southern Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in &lt;a href=\"Splintered%20Souls\"&gt;Splintered Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSentinel's Stand takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Gully%20of%20Madness\"&gt;Gully of Madness&lt;/a&gt;. Here, the player races through the gully, summoning defensive towers with abilities like freeze and chain lightning to prevent shard-warped creatures from reaching a massive shardstorm and wreaking havoc on the land. Should the player succeed, they can gain &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "42592", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42592", "title": "Sentinel's Watch", "text": "Sentinel's Watch is the outpost of the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt; upon &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nSentinel's Watch was manned by the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;, and provided protection for the region and &lt;a href=\"Razed%20Village\"&gt;the nearby village&lt;/a&gt;. The outpost has three entrances to the west, east, and south, which all ultimately lead to the outpost proper. A barracks is also maintained.\nUnfortunately, the outpost lacked sufficient funding and its guards regularly underfed. &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; occasionally sent supplies but it was not enough. Because of this, merchants that opened shop at because of the safety of the location were taxed.\nHistory.\nKhazra Aggression.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the village came under attack by &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt;, and its people fled to the outpost. The outpost itself came under attack as well, and it was believed that it was only a matter of time before the fortress's overwhelmed and underequipped soldiers were swallowed up. The khazra attacked the outpost on two fronts, and Captain &lt;a href=\"Vereks\"&gt;Vereks&lt;/a&gt; knew that unless the situation changed, they would be forced to abandon the outpost.\nSalvation came in the form of a &lt;a href=\"Monks%20of%20Ivgorod\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Oza\"&gt;Oza&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;. Vereks requested that Oza stay at the fort to help defend it, and in doing so, the khazra would be cut off from reinforcing the village. Meanwhile, the Shard-seeker and Lieutenant &lt;a href=\"Ralvar\"&gt;Ralvar&lt;/a&gt; would clear out the khazra in the village. A bold plan, but as Ralvar pointed out, bold plans were all the outpost had left. Before the plan could be enacted, however, the khazra launched another assault, giving the defenders barely enough time to react. The khazra quickly made it into the outpost, killing at least &lt;a href=\"Cavil\"&gt;one guard&lt;/a&gt;, along with taking a number of captives. Ralvar ordered the perimeter guards to fall back to the gate and use the path to limit the effectiveness of the khazra's numbers, while he and the Shard-seeker headed to retrieve the captives.\nForgotten Nightmares.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231271\"&gt;A year later&lt;/a&gt;, foreboding &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;Black Mists&lt;/a&gt; began to emanate from the &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monastery\"&gt;Silent Monastery&lt;/a&gt;, threatening to cover the entire mountain in darkness. The fog began to creep into Sentinel's Watch.\nIn-game.\nSentinel's Watch is the safe zone of Mount Zavain in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located at the start of the area, and borders the &lt;a href=\"Foggy%20Plains\"&gt;Foggy Plains&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "34063", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34063", "title": "Sentinel (Diablo I)", "text": "Sentinel (misspelled Sentinal in earliest versions) was a spell in demo version of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". In the released game, it was cut and replaced with .\nGeneral Information.\nMuch like Guardian, Sentinel used to summon an eyeball that hovered beside the character, traveling with them. At any foes within certain range, it would shoot s at no Mana cost, attacking all enemies close enough at once. \nIt lagged behind the character a bit, and could be led into a room, then left inside with the monsters if one hurried out and shut the door. Monsters did not attack the Sentinel, as it was untargetable.\nThe spell was still operational in Beta, and all the related files are still present in the Retail version, but the format of the graphic files wasn't converted from *.cel to *.cl2."}
