{"id": "20794", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20794", "title": "Seven Sins", "text": "The Seven Sins are &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; crafted pauldrons in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They require character level 60 to be worn. Their level 70 equivalent is &lt;a href=\"Corruption\"&gt;Corruption&lt;/a&gt;.\nInterestingly, Seven Sins have nine properties, as opposed to the game's normal allotment of six properties. This may be in part due to the similar boost to all Core stats that the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Ring%20of%20the%20Zodiac\"&gt;Obsidian Ring of the Zodiac&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0used to have.\nCrafting.\nThe Seven Sins can be crafted using the Plan: Seven Sins, 42000 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;, 15 &lt;a href=\"Reusable%20Parts\"&gt;Reusable Parts&lt;/a&gt;, 15 &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Dust\"&gt;Arcane Dust&lt;/a&gt; and 20 &lt;a href=\"Veiled%20Crystal\"&gt;Veiled Crystal&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "5993", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5993", "title": "Seven Tombs", "text": ""}
{"id": "1660", "revid": "44771288", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1660", "title": "Seven Tombs (Quest)", "text": "The Seven Tombs is the sixth and final quest of &lt;a href=\"The%20Secret%20of%20the%20Vizjerei\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt;. It is initiated by talking to &lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt; after either completing &lt;a href=\"Radament%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Radament's Lair&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Staff%20%28quest%29\"&gt;The Horadric Staff&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Tainted%20Sun\"&gt;Tainted Sun&lt;/a&gt; quests or after the player character reaches level 20. The goal of the quest is to find the true tomb, gain entrance to &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Chamber\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Chamber&lt;/a&gt;, and destroy &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; before &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; manages to free him. The quest is completed after the defeat of the demon &lt;a href=\"Duriel\"&gt;Duriel&lt;/a&gt; and then having the player character speak to the Archangel &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\n&lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Drognan\"&gt;Drognan&lt;/a&gt; concluded that the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wanderer\"&gt;Dark Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; who had passed through &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; shortly before the arrival of the player character was Diablo himself. Diablo was set on freeing his brother Baal, who was imprisoned within &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; centuries ago. Tal Rasha's Tomb lay hidden deep in the desert amongst six other tombs.\nWalkthrough.\nThis quest is more or less embedded within the other quests. First, a &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Staff%20%28item%29\"&gt;Horadric Staff&lt;/a&gt; had to be created in order to gain entrance to Tal Rasha's Chamber in &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Staff%20%28quest%29\"&gt;The Horadric Staff&lt;/a&gt; quest. Then, &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha\"&gt;Tal Rasha&lt;/a&gt;'s Tomb itself had to be found by searching the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Arcane Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; for clues in the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Sanctuary%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Arcane Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; quest. Once &lt;a href=\"Horazon%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Horazon's Journal&lt;/a&gt; has been read, the glyph of the True Tomb is recorded in the quest log, and a portal opens to the &lt;a href=\"Canyon%20of%20the%20Magi\"&gt;Canyon of the Magi&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the Canyon of the Magi, the tomb that bears that same glyph is the true tomb of Tal Rasha. The true tomb is considerably larger than the false tombs. It might be worthwhile to explore the false tombs though, since there are plenty of &lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; and golden &lt;a href=\"Chests%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;chests&lt;/a&gt; waiting inside.\nIn the depths of the true tomb, there is a circular formation on the ground with an Orifice in the center. Click on the Orifice and place the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Staff%20%28item%29\"&gt;Horadric Staff&lt;/a&gt; into the slot of the special window that pops up. A passage opens up in the wall, which leads to &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Chamber\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Chamber&lt;/a&gt;. This is where &lt;a href=\"Duriel\"&gt;Duriel&lt;/a&gt; stands guard to fight intruders. After defeating Duriel, explore the Chamber and find &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;. After listening to Tyrael, a portal to &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; opens. Take the portal and speak to &lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt;. He will inform the player that &lt;a href=\"Meshif\"&gt;Meshif&lt;/a&gt; will take him/her east to &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, the location of &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nUse a &lt;a href=\"Town%20Portal\"&gt;Town Portal&lt;/a&gt; scroll \"before\" entering the Chamber, in order to stock up on &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Potions\"&gt;Healing Potions&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thawing%20Potion\"&gt;Thawing Potion&lt;/a&gt;s in preparation for the tough battle. The Chamber has no exit, so opening another Town Portal upon entry is recommended for a quick ecape route. Duriel is a tough melee boss that is oriented around cold-based attacks. He also has a cold aura identical to the Paladin's &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Freeze\"&gt;Holy Freeze&lt;/a&gt;."}
