{"id": "21172", "revid": "44564686", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21172", "title": "Sever", "text": "Sever is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 50 to drop.\nThis is the only weapon past patch 2.0 to retain its '&lt;a href=\"slain%20enemies%20rest%20in%20pieces\"&gt;slain enemies rest in pieces&lt;/a&gt;' property.\nIt is also the only weapon with bonus damage against &lt;a href=\"demons\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally, the &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt; explosion effect was achieved by adding a huge portion of damage to a monster (already dead by that moment). However, it was scrapped when players found an unintended use for it in form of skills and items that allow dealing part of damage to surrounding foes."}
