{"id": "49953", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49953", "title": "Seysild the Surveyor", "text": "Seysild is a &lt;a href=\"witch\"&gt;witch&lt;/a&gt;, and a member of the &lt;a href=\"Untameable%20Wilds\"&gt;Untameable Wilds&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circle\"&gt;Circle&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nSeysild is the surveyor of the Untameable Wilds. She was named after &lt;a href=\"Seysild\"&gt;a notable witch of times past&lt;/a&gt;. Her name made people to have high expectations for her, likely expecting her to live up to her namesake.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;Voidwound&lt;/a&gt; was freed, though they were later defeated, with the wardkeeper playing a role in the defeat of &lt;a href=\"Catarag%20the%20Strangling%20Sun\"&gt;Catarag the Strangling Sun&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;Nisza&lt;/a&gt; returned after Catarag's &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; with tales of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;an adventurer/group of adventurers&lt;/a&gt; who played a major role in the fight against the Voidwound. Later, the Prima saw a vision of &lt;a href=\"Shardborne\"&gt;a new evil&lt;/a&gt; rising from the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Dreadlands\"&gt;Southern Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shardstorms\"&gt;storms&lt;/a&gt; made out of shards of &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;creation&lt;/a&gt;. Seysild followed Nisza to &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, eager to meet the person she heard tales about. When she met them, she asked for them to help her acquire some of the shards.\nIn-game.\nSeysild was introduced to \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" in the &lt;a href=\"Splintered%20Souls\"&gt;Splintered Souls&lt;/a&gt; update. She could be found near &lt;a href=\"Rakkis%20Square\"&gt;Rakkis Square&lt;/a&gt;, where she could direct players to &lt;a href=\"shardstorms\"&gt;shardstorms&lt;/a&gt;. The player could stymie them for rewards.\nThe shardstorms could be found in one of the wilderness zones, with the location changing each day. There were three separate shardstorms in the designated zone each day.\nThis feature was removed in the &lt;a href=\"Precipice%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Precipice of Horror&lt;/a&gt; without announcement."}
