{"id": "48295", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48295", "title": "Shadow Assembly", "text": "The is an event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" that occurs every day except Sunday between 12pm-2pm and 7pm-9pm.\nGameplay.\nDuring the event period, players can gather in the Assembly Hall (accessed via &lt;a href=\"Court%20of%20Whispers\"&gt;Court of Whispers&lt;/a&gt;) with the aim to collect 4 Akeba's Blessings (Strength, Vision, Sacrifice, Cunning).\nThe event is subdivided into cycles of 2 minutes each. The firs 10 seconds are for \"preparing the blessings\" and the remaining time is for sharing them. Players are randomly selected as blessers, and get the icon of the blessing next to their name. Only the blessers can share blessings with other players, and each blesser can only do so 4 times whenever they are selected. Sharing a blessing awards a random piece of equipment. Other players must wait for a blesser to bless them, and may request blessings every 10 seconds.\nRewards.\nDuring the event, an entry appears in the quest log that shows which blessings you have collected. Clicking on this entry brings up a window where you can claim the rewards. These include EXP, 250 &lt;a href=\"Marks\"&gt;Marks&lt;/a&gt; and 3 &lt;a href=\"Aspirant%27s%20Key\"&gt;Aspirant's Key&lt;/a&gt;s per blessing. Any unclaimed rewards are sent via mail after the event time expires.\nHistory.\nOriginally the Assembly only ran between 7pm-9pm. An additional 12pm-2pm time slot was added in the September 21 2023 update."}
{"id": "9444", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9444", "title": "Shadow Beast", "text": "Shadow Beasts are a type of &lt;a href=\"Scavenger%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Scavenger&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" may summon creatures called Shadow Beasts for their &lt;a href=\"Rain%20of%20Vengeance\"&gt;Rain of Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; skill, but these are completely different, and appear more like &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Hellflyer\"&gt;Demonic Hellflyer&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn-game.\nDiablo I.\nShadow Beasts are encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\", found on the lower levels of the labyrinth. They have a fierce attack.\nHeroes of the Storm.\nShadow Beasts can be summoned by &lt;a href=\"Valla\"&gt;Valla&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Heroes%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heroes of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "4950", "revid": "13298744", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4950", "title": "Shadow Bow", "text": "The Shadow Bow is an Elite &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bow&lt;/a&gt; found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "32275", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32275", "title": "Shadow Clone", "text": "Shadow Clones are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; in the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" series. They serve as shadowy replicas of various heroes.\nDiablo Immortal.\nShadow Clones appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt; summons shadow clones in the form of every &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;playable class&lt;/a&gt;. They also act as the &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Zone%20Trial\"&gt;Zone Trial&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Purify%20the%20Corruption\"&gt;Purify the Corruption&lt;/a&gt;\", where they are a copy of the player with all their unlocked skills, though they lack the Legendary variants of their skills. A super unique shadow clone is &lt;a href=\"Hemlir%27s%20Shadow%20Clone\"&gt;Hemlir's Shadow Clone&lt;/a&gt;.\nA Shadow Clone also features in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Controlled%20Burn\"&gt;Controlled Burn&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo III.\nShadow Clones make their debut in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are dark apparitions summoned by in the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Realm of Terror&lt;/a&gt;. One may encounter them in , during the second phase of the final battle with the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evil\"&gt;Prime Evil&lt;/a&gt;.\nJudging by Diablo's speech, they serve as a symbolic representation of &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;'s own fear, which they must defeat to escape the dark grasp of the Realm of Terror.\nThey mimic the appearance of the Nephalem heroes, although they are pitch dark in color (except for their equipped weapon), and are classified as &lt;a href=\"Demons\"&gt;Demons&lt;/a&gt;. Their damage and &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; do not scale with those of the character, but are immense compared to normal monsters, therefore each Shadow Clone is a formidable foe.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Haunt%20of%20Vaxo\"&gt;Haunt of Vaxo&lt;/a&gt; also allows the summoning of Shadow Clones of the player, but these clones fight at the player's side for 15 seconds. They function in the same manner as Shadow Clones created by Diablo, except that their Life and damage do match those of the character. These clones (and the &lt;a href=\"%23Season%2022%20Bonus\"&gt;Season 22 clones&lt;/a&gt;) will follow the hero within the current zone but will not move to a new zone with the player. This includes &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Rift\"&gt;Nephalem Rift&lt;/a&gt; levels and Greater Rift floors. If the player returns to the zone within the lifespan of the clone, it will be there waiting. &lt;a href=\"Town%20Portal\"&gt;Town Portal&lt;/a&gt;s have the same effect, leaving the clone behind, waiting. \nIn the console version of the game, a &lt;a href=\"Nemesis%20Kills\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt; may summon a Shadow Clone of each player it has slain.\nIn battle, Clones use the characters' own skills, not necessarily those currently equipped. Each clone has a fixed set of 1-3 abilities, randomly chosen in each game (meaning that in each battle, no matter how many Clones spawn and no matter the number of attempts, their skill set will remain same). Each ability will benefit from a predetermined &lt;a href=\"skill%20rune\"&gt;skill rune&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Note\": on some occasions, other skills or skill runes have been reported; however, Shapeshift skills, summoning of &lt;a href=\"pets\"&gt;pets&lt;/a&gt; (with the exception of ), &lt;a href=\"healing\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"absorption\"&gt;absorption&lt;/a&gt; skills are never used by Shadow Clones.\nSeason 22 Bonus.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 22, activating a or Pylon will spawn in a shadow clone of the same class. This clone will chosen at random out of 3 predetermined builds with 6 active skills and no passives. The shadow clone's power will scale with the stats of the player and will last for up to 1 minute or until the player dies.\nNote that while some pre-set variations are themed around certain &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt;, others are centered around thematic ability mechanics. Equipped items and sets have no effect on Shadow Clones besides empowering their stats: their skills only have the basic and Skill Rune effects. However, the effects that increase damage taken by enemies from allies do work."}
{"id": "6436", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6436", "title": "Shadow Dancer", "text": "Shadow Dancer are &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Myrmidon%20Greaves\"&gt;Myrmidon Greaves&lt;/a&gt;.\nIntended for &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; use, Shadow Dancer has the highest kick damage of all boots thanks to its base type, as well as a good boost to &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Disciplines\"&gt;Shadow Disciplines&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\nDefense: 122-144\nRequired Level: 71\nRequired Strength: 167\nDurability: 24\nAssassin Kick Damage: 83-149"}
{"id": "4859", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4859", "title": "Shadow Disciplines", "text": "To remain protected from exposure to the potential corruption of magic, &lt;a href=\"Assassins\"&gt;Assassins&lt;/a&gt; must defeat their sorcerous opponents without actually using spells themselves. To this end, they have mastered the clandestine talents, as well as the arts of obfuscation, and honed their latent psychic abilities to develop the Shadow Disciplines. These skills represent the end result of generations of strict mental conditioning and intensive stealth training.\nThis set of skills adds to the mystery and power of the Assassin. The Shadow Disciplines don't make the attacks, they make the attacks better. They don't hide the Assassin, they make her harder to see. They can also cause poison damage and summon a Shadow Warrior to fight at the Assassin's side. In short, the Shadow Disciplines are a set of very important skills that augment the Assassin's other skill sets, while still providing a great set of unique and devastating abilities.\nUsage Notes.\n&lt;a href=\"Burst%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Burst of Speed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fade\"&gt;Fade&lt;/a&gt; cannot be used at the same time. You can only use one of them at a time.\nYou can have a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Warrior\"&gt;Shadow Warrior&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Master\"&gt;Shadow Master&lt;/a&gt; but you cannot have both at the same time.\nThe \"active\" skills like &lt;a href=\"Burst%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Burst of Speed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fade\"&gt;Fade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Shadows\"&gt;Cloak of Shadows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Warrior\"&gt;Shadow Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Master\"&gt;Shadow Master&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Venom\"&gt;Venom&lt;/a&gt; can still retain their effects when you swap weapons. Therefore, if your secondary set has better bonuses to Shadow Disciplines skills, you can activate the skills with this set and then swap back to your primary set to be used for combat."}
{"id": "6629", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6629", "title": "Shadow Killer", "text": "Shadow Killer is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Cestus\"&gt;Battle Cestus&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nWith an affinity for &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt;, Shadow Killer is useful for impairing enemies, chilling them with cold; it has a fairly high chance of casting on striking, a good crowd-control skill. Still, in mode, Shadow Killer may not be as effective due to reduced cold duration.\nStats.\nDamage: (145-172) To (170-201) \nRequired Level: 78\nRequired Strength: 100\nRequired Dexterity: 100\nKatar Class - Very Fast Attack Speed"}
