{"id": "42604", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42604", "title": "Shadow War", "text": "Shadow War is a &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt;-exclusive game mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", where Shadow Clans battle one another.\nThe battle format is similar to &lt;a href=\"Alley%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Alley of Blood&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlayers can sign up to a Shadow War starting 9 p.m. on Tuesday. Each war consists of 3-12 individual matches in different categories: Eminent, Exalted, Famed, and Proud. Each category gives a certain number of points for a win, and the clan with the most points wins the war. The event begins at 7:35 p.m. server time on Thursdays for the Preliminary Round and 7:35 p.m. server time on Saturdays for the Final and Third Place Playoff Rounds. The countdown to the Shadow War's beginning will start at 7:30 p.m. server time to give players enough time to gather and organize for their fight.\nThe feature decides the top ten dark clans that go on to the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;. Players that engage in the Shadow War are rewarded with experience and a guaranteed random &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20item\"&gt;Legendary item&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe clan leader and officers have access to a management tool that allows setting requirements on participation in each category.\nServer Merge.\nShadow War is skipped during a week of a &lt;a href=\"server%20merge\"&gt;server merge&lt;/a&gt; - the sign up button does not work, and the brackets will be empty. The \"Top 10\" page will display no clans for the rest of the week after the merge.\nHistory.\nBefore the September 21 2023 update, Shadow War used the same battle format as the &lt;a href=\"Challenge%20of%20the%20Immortal\"&gt;Challenge of the Immortal&lt;/a&gt; component of the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;, with the clan leader controlling the Immortal on the opposing clan's side.\nThe management tool was added in the update."}
{"id": "4877", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4877", "title": "Shadow Warrior", "text": "Shadow Warrior is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"The Assassin trained in this discipline has the ability to project a \"shadow\" of herself. The Shadow Warrior makes use of normal attack and the two skills the Assassin has readied for herself. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nWith this skill, one can summon a copy of themselves that can use the two abilities assigned to the left and right mouse buttons at any given time while the Shadow Warrior is alive (though it cannot cast Shadow Warrior or &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Master\"&gt;Shadow Master&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe level of the skills the Shadow Warrior uses are equivalent to 1/3 of its own skill level + 1/2 of the level of the skill being used, rounded up.\nTraps that the Warrior (or Master) lays out will also count towards the user's total limit of traps, potentially overriding their own trap placement. Shadow Warrior gains +4 resistance to all per level, to a max of level 75.\nShadow Warrior is one of the few spells the Assassin may cast within a &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;. Once cast, the Shadow Warrior stays with the player until she is destroyed, at which point a new one can be created. This includes moving between Acts. When injured, a shadow warrior heals over time. If the player saves and quits, however, the shadow warrior must be resummoned when the game resumes.\nThe Items for Shadow Warrior:\nHidden Stats.\n&lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;\nShadow Warriors have a base strength and dexterity equal to their level * 10. Also, the Shadow Warrior gains +4 resistance to all per level, to a max of level 75."}
