{"id": "144", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=144", "title": "Shadow Wolf Tribe", "text": "The Shadow Wolf Tribe (a.k.a. Shadow Wolves) is a tribe, \nLore.\nThe berserk &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt;s of the Shadow Wolf Tribe lose themselves to such frenzy that they cannot contain the force of their blows.\nThe Shadow Wolves are masters of the &lt;a href=\"axe\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;, and with the weapon, they seek to match the swiping claws and the biting teeth of the wolves that they lived with and fought beside. The first axes were but crude stones mounted on wooden shafts. But after the Barbarians learned the secret of steel and swords from &lt;a href=\"Bul-Kathos\"&gt;Bul-Kathos&lt;/a&gt;, the axe soon fell into disfavor. Not long before the Worldstone's destruction however, warriors and smiths from the steppes perfected the axe as a weapon equal to (or greater than) the &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;. The Shadow Wolf Tribe once again taught the swift and terrible power of the axe to those who wish to learn how to cull the weak from the herd and protect their pack from the legions of &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;. \nTheir axes are buried alongside the warriors, or passed on to another warrior.\nHistory.\nThe tribe was formed prior to the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;. They once created &lt;a href=\"Shocking%20Chaos\"&gt;a pauldron&lt;/a&gt; from fangs torn from threats to the tribe.\nThe were in &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; when the city was sieged by the &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Army of Destruction&lt;/a&gt;. As the city fell, numerous warriors fled the city with their young and old, and with &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s in hot pursuit. Most of the warriors stayed behind at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;plains&lt;/a&gt; to south of Sescheron in order to give the rest time to escape. They were successful after a bloody battle, but many of them lost their lives. The survivors settled down in a &lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;village&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"Everfrost%20Lake\"&gt;Everfrost Lake&lt;/a&gt;."}
