{"id": "26489", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26489", "title": "Shadow of Death", "text": "Shadows of Death are &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Reapers\"&gt;Reaper&lt;/a&gt; monsters encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", .\nIn-game.\nShadows of Death are absolutely identical to &lt;a href=\"Phantasm\"&gt;Phantasm&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Wraiths&lt;/a&gt; in terms of their abilities, but count as Reapers rather than Undead for targeting purposes. They have a melee slashing attack, as well as ranged life drain attack that causes heavy &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage at medium distance and slows the victim down. Unlike Phantasms, Shadows prefer to engage enemy in melee. They move quickly and may phase through all kinds of obstacles and impassable terrain, often using it to avoid being hit, spread out or to approach the player from unexpected direction.\nIn addition to that, a &lt;a href=\"Summoner%20of%20the%20Dead\"&gt;Summoner of the Dead&lt;/a&gt; may create Shadows of Death. However, when the Summoner is dead, all his Shadows disperse that instant."}
{"id": "52257", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52257", "title": "Shadow of the Frozen Throne", "text": " was a crossover event between \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"World%20of%20Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\". It ran from July 4th to 26th, 2024.\nGameplay.\n&lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Gate\"&gt;Frozen Gate&lt;/a&gt;s appeared at random points in the wilderness. Entering it lead the player to a reminiscent of a shortened &lt;a href=\"Mad%20King%27s%20Breach\"&gt;Mad King's Breach&lt;/a&gt;. While in the dungeon, player were awarded Chill of the Frozen Throne; a buff that increases damage by for seconds for every 5 monsters killed. Additionally, &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s are randomly raised to fight for the player (up to 5 at a time)."}
