{"id": "13024", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13024", "title": "Shadowcrow", "text": "Shadowcrow is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20One%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Dark One&lt;/a&gt; found on &lt;a href=\"Level%205%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;level five&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\", that is gray in color and wields an orange colored shield. He doesn't have magic immunities or magic resistances but gives off a small light radius. He is very weak compared to other unique monsters, but has the ability to hide like &lt;a href=\"Hidden\"&gt;Hiddens&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "9351", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9351", "title": "Shadowdrinker", "text": "Shadowdrinker is a bright yellow &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%23Diablo%20I\"&gt;Horror Captain&lt;/a&gt; encountered on in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe is a special monster due to a unique special ability: he is able to bury beneath the ground and sneak past characters, only materializing on the surface to attack. This would make him a formidable foe if there wasn't one vital disadvantage\u2014his light radius betrays his position wherever he is even when dug in, so it is easy to prevent surprise attacks and attack him from range while he approaches beneath the surface. Apart from his special ability he is only slightly stronger than normal Horror Captains. He is colored similarly to &lt;a href=\"Illusion%20Weaver\"&gt;Illusion Weavers&lt;/a&gt;. \nYou can know he's near, when you encounter stronger &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Horrors&lt;/a&gt; burrying into the ground."}
