{"id": "2602", "revid": "9305822", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2602", "title": "Shadowfang", "text": "Shadowfang is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAlthough it is significantly stronger when wielded with two hands, Shadowfang has little useful bonuses that can effectively be carried on later in game.\nOne of its most striking features is its added &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage. Although its damage is moderate at best, it does &lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;slow&lt;/a&gt; enemies for a fair amount of time. Despite the fact that cold duration is decreased in and &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;, compared to other unique &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt; with similar effects such as &lt;a href=\"Gleamscythe\"&gt;Gleamscythe&lt;/a&gt;, its cold duration is far longer.\nShadowfang also provides &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; leech, both useful for many physical fighters. Its increased &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Resist\"&gt;Cold Resist&lt;/a&gt; seems rather arbitrary, but its decreased &lt;a href=\"Light%20Radius\"&gt;Light Radius&lt;/a&gt; may also be useful for physical fighters, since it prevents enemy archers and mages from seeing them sooner.\nIt appears green in-game.\nLore.\nShadowfang is a type of &lt;a href=\"demonblade\"&gt;demonblade&lt;/a&gt;. It was constructed at the &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Izual\"&gt;Izual&lt;/a&gt; launched an assault to prevent its completion, but failed, and was taken captive.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 4 To 18\nTwo-Hand Damage: 16 To 34\nRequired Level: 12\nRequired Strength: 35\nRequired Dexterity: 27\nDurability: 44Sword Class - Fast Attack Speed"}
