{"id": "48102", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48102", "title": "Shady Stock", "text": "Shady Stock is a recurring &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;seasonal&lt;/a&gt; event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nThe event lasts for a week, starting on the second Saturday of the season and ending just before midnight on the next Friday. During the event there are four daily tasks to complete, each rewarding Shady Tokens:\nFor 100 tokens, a Mystery &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Item\"&gt;Legendary Item&lt;/a&gt; can be purchased from Yakin. Purchasing 3 of these unlocks a Mystery &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Item&lt;/a&gt; that can be claimed once per character per season.\nOnce the event expires, leftover Shady Tokens are converted into gold.\nHistory.\nThe Seal of Triumph rewards were added with the May 11-18 2024 run of the event (the first time it was part of &lt;a href=\"Event%20Center%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Event Center&lt;/a&gt;).\nSome time before August 30, 2024, the dungeon task was changed from a Bonus Drop Dungeon to a Random Dungeon. In the old version, using the Random Dungeon feature would not complete this by itself, even though using it rewards bonus drops, however if the random dungeon picked was one that has bonus drops for the week, it would count."}
