{"id": "52442", "revid": "46404728", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52442", "title": "Sharval Wilds", "text": "The Sharval Wilds are located in &lt;a href=\"Entsteig\"&gt;Entsteig&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Wilds are apparently inimical to &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; life, and it is said that mere survival in Sharval demands compromises of both body and &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;. The people of Entsteig believe the Wilds to be an enchanted place of fey spirits. Many of Entsteig's old customs and pagan rituals dating from before the kingdom's conversion to &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; are still practiced by Entsteig's inhabitants in the Wilds\nAfter the Great Enmity, the Zakarum faith still holds sway in the region, though it has come to a kind of a truce with the old gods and myths of the Wilds' folk traditions. The forested lands and the wolves of the region reminded &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath Nahr&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt; in some ways, though in other ways he found it to be a far stranger place.\n is home to the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circle\"&gt;Witch Circle&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "41837", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41837", "title": "Shassar", "text": ""}
{"id": "37470", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37470", "title": "Shassar Sea", "text": "The Shassar Sea is a desert located in far eastern &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt;, well past &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nShassar is a dry land, where food and water are in short supply. It has been indicated that the Shassar Sea was once an actual body of water, but if so, this ceased to be the case. The ruins of docks and boats can still be found on the sands. During the reign of King &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;, Shassar was far from the wasteland it would eventually become.\nSandstorms are a potential threat for anyone traveling across the desert. It is said that the three most dangerous killers in Shassar are scorpion stings, snake venom, and time itself.\nA number of desert gangs vie for control of Shassar, foremost among them the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Blades\"&gt;Amber Blades&lt;/a&gt;.\nEarly History.\nThe Shassar Sea was once home to the &lt;a href=\"Fahiran%20Empire\"&gt;Fahiran Empire&lt;/a&gt;, and at the time of its fall, was ruled by King &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;. After his &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, the people turned on each other, trying to claim his riches. His &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;scepter&lt;/a&gt;, the symbol of his authority, was split into three parts, which appears to have hindered his subjects' ability to have found an heir. \nBy the 13th century, the Shassar civilization had collapsed, its people scattered throughout the land. Shassar itself turned into a wasteland.\nRecent History.\nOver the years, many adventurers came to Shassar, seeking to loot its tombs. However, none of them made it out alive.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the Shassar Sea had a grim reputation. &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; sought to trade with Shassar's merchants, but the &lt;a href=\"lacuni\"&gt;lacuni&lt;/a&gt; and other &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s that prowled the sands hindered this. It offered &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; to clear them out, but adventurers in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; refused to take bounties that would take them to the region. &lt;a href=\"Vataos\"&gt;Vataos&lt;/a&gt; terrorized Shassar's scattered people. However, with the reconstituted Scepter of Fahir coming into the hands of &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;Tabri&lt;/a&gt; (leader of the &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Blades\"&gt;Amber Blades&lt;/a&gt;), she declared that she had the right to rule the land, and a symbol through which Shassar's people could rally behind, against Vataos. &lt;a href=\"Peth\"&gt;Peth&lt;/a&gt; later stated that the Blades intended to retake Shassar. Despite this, the Blades' attempts at retaking Shassar were stymied by the &lt;a href=\"lacuni\"&gt;lacuni&lt;/a&gt;, who attacked one of their villages, killing dozens and causing the survivors to flee. Unable to retake it on their own, the Blades requested aid from any able-bodied fighters in Westmarch.\nIn-game.\nThe area can be explored in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a 'hub zone,' and has a recommended &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of 28-36."}
