{"id": "5529", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5529", "title": "Shenk the Overseer", "text": "Shenk the Overseer is an &lt;a href=\"Overseer\"&gt;Overseer&lt;/a&gt; and one of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s most vicious generals. He is found at the end of the &lt;a href=\"Bloody%20Foothills\"&gt;Bloody Foothills&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28Act%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of\u00a0\"\".\nThis ruthless taskmaster inflicts &lt;a href=\"Minion%20Frenzy\"&gt;Minion Frenzy&lt;/a&gt; on his &lt;a href=\"Enslaved\"&gt;Enslaved&lt;/a&gt; minions around him, turning them into &lt;a href=\"Fanatic%20Enslaved\"&gt;Fanatic Enslaved&lt;/a&gt;. He must be killed in order to complete the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20on%20Harrogath\"&gt;Siege on Harrogath&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nHe is also one of the few Super Unique enemies in the game that does not have any minions, though he has a lot of non-direct ones.\nAbilities:"}
{"id": "32667", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32667", "title": "Shenlong", "text": "Shenlong was a &lt;a href=\"Veradani\"&gt;Veradani&lt;/a&gt; master. Many claim that he is a myth, though those who have felt the unrelenting fury of his wrath would argue otherwise."}
{"id": "27855", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27855", "title": "Shenlong's Fist of Legend", "text": "Shenlong's Fist of Legend\u00a0is one of the two &lt;a href=\"Fist%20Weapons\"&gt;Fist Weapons&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Shenlong%27s%20Spirit\"&gt;Shenlong's Spirit&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a060 to drop.\nPrior to patch 2.1, it was one of the few weapons with &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt; Damage affix."}
{"id": "27857", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27857", "title": "Shenlong's Relentless Assault", "text": "Shenlong's Relentless Assault\u00a0is one of the two &lt;a href=\"Fist%20Weapons\"&gt;Fist Weapons&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Shenlong%27s%20Spirit\"&gt;Shenlong's Spirit&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a060 to drop."}
{"id": "27853", "revid": "43723075", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27853", "title": "Shenlong's Spirit", "text": "Shenlong's Spirit\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;-only minor class\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThis set is named after legendary Master &lt;a href=\"Shenlong\"&gt;Shenlong&lt;/a&gt;. It requires a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of 60.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of just two items, both of which are required to complete the set. Both pieces are Monk-only.\nSet Bonuses (2 pieces):\nThe second part of set bonus is not passive: it triggers when maximum Spirit is actually reached, and lasts until the Monk loses all Spirit. The zero Spirit regeneration is also \"not\" passive, and only active during the damage amplification phase: it sets spirit regeneration to -65 per second, regardless of previous value.\nWith proper build, this allows Primary skills to deliver tremendous amounts of damage, especially when coupled with &lt;a href=\"Raiment%20of%20a%20Thousand%20Storms\"&gt;Raiment of a Thousand Storms&lt;/a&gt; set and passive effects like &lt;a href=\"Depth%20Diggers\"&gt;Depth Diggers&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe 350% damage modifier at maximum Spirit is multiplicative to other similar bonuses.\nSpirit Generators only include Primary skills, not other skills that replenish any Spirit: &lt;a href=\"Fists%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Fists of Thunder&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Deadly%20Reach\"&gt;Deadly Reach&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crippling%20Wave\"&gt;Crippling Wave&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Hundred%20Fists\"&gt;Way of the Hundred Fists&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince the Spirit drain is static (65 per second, \"not\" per tick), this bonus is especially effective with &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt; boosts like &lt;a href=\"Flying%20Dragon\"&gt;Flying Dragon&lt;/a&gt;. This set also works well with &lt;a href=\"Raiment%20of%20a%20Thousand%20Storms\"&gt;Raiment of a Thousand Storms&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Inna%27s%20Mantra\"&gt;Inna's Mantra&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nOld (Pre-2.3) set bonus:\nThe chance was roughly 25%, unaffected by the &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt;, and had a [3 / Attacks per Second] seconds internal &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;. The ball traveled 60 yards in a straight line, dealing 1200% damage as &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to enemies it pierced though."}
